{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778778992171,"sessionID":"ses_1d88e89c9ffe10UZsjE0ogWbPr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r10s0\ntitle: Share ALU multipliers into single unsigned product with correction\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The bench ALU currently computes three separate 32×32 products\n  (signed×signed, unsigned×unsigned, signed×unsigned). Yosys does not\n  merge them, so the design pays for three multipliers worth of DSP/LUT\n  area.  With LUT4 already at 9927/10000, placement congestion is severe\n  and likely limits the achievable Fmax of the fast integer path.\n  Removing two of the three multipliers frees substantial area without\n  changing IPC or adding pipeline stages.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace mul_ss, mul_uu and mul_su with a single unsigned×unsigned\n  product.  MUL/MULHU reuse the low/high halves directly.  MULH and\n  MULHSU high halves are recovered with a cheap 32-bit correction\n  subtractor: MULHSU subtracts b when a is negative; MULH additionally\n  subtracts a when b is negative.  The ALTOPS formal branch and the\n  divider path are untouched, and the fast-path 2:1 mux is preserved.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: Collapse three multipliers into one unsigned product; add correction subtractors for MULH/MULHSU high halves.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r10s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r10s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r10s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778778992158,"end":1778778992170}},"id":"pr