mul_uu[31:0]). All other M-extension opcodes are\\n  removed from the ALU result mux.\\n- The new `rtl/mdu.sv` module handles the cold ops:\\n    * DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU using a 32-cycle iterative restoring divider.\\n    * MULH/MULHU/MULHSU using a 2-cycle pipelined 33x33 multiplier whose\\n      high-half result is captured in a registered output.\\n  The divider reuses the proven `div_unit.sv` state machine pattern from\\n  the reference v1 core, adapted for the bench baseline.\\n- `rtl/ex_stage.sv` detects a cold M-extension opcode and asserts a new\\n  `ex_long_busy` signal to the hazard unit, freezing the pipeline until the\\n  MDU signals `done`. On completion the MDU result is written into the\\n  EX/MEM register exactly like a normal ALU result.\\n- The ALTOPS branch in the MDU mirrors the formal substitutions already\\n  present in the baseline ALU, so `make formal` behavior is unchanged.\\n\\nCoreMark should see zero IPC penalty because its timed loop contains no\\nDIV/REM and no MULH variants, while the common RV32I and MUL instructions\\nnow run on a shorter critical path. LUT utilization should drop by\\n~1500-2500, relieving routing congestion and raising median Fmax.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases and MULH/MULHU/MULHSU cases from the\\nmain result mux. Keep only the hot RV32I ops plus ALU_MUL (low half\\nof mul_uu). Add a cold-op indicator bit or reuse op[4] so EX stage\\ncan detect when the MDU is needed.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mdu.sv\", \"description\": \"New module: registered 2-cycle high-half multiplier for MULH/MULHU/\\nMULHSU plus a 32-cycle iterative divider for DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU.\\nIncludes start/busy/done handshake, ALTOPS substitutions under\\n`RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS`, and exact RV32M corner-case handling.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate MDU, route operands to it, detect cold M-op via opcode\\nencoding, assert `ex_long_busy` while MDU is active, and select MDU\\nresult into EX/MEM when done.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `ex_long_busy` alongside existing `dmem_ready` / `imem_ready`\\nstall sources. Treat MDU busy like a dmem stall: freeze IF/ID/EX\\nand bubble EX/MEM until the unit completes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `ex_long_busy` signal from ex_stage into hazard_unit.\\nNo top-level IO changes.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases and MULH/MULHU/MULHSU cases from the\\nmain result mux. Keep only the hot RV32I ops plus ALU_MUL (low half\\nof mul_uu). Add a cold-op indicator bit or reuse op[4] so EX stage\\ncan detect when the MDU is needed.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mdu.sv\", \"description\": \"New module: registered 2-cycle high-half multiplier for MULH/MULHU/\\nMULHSU plus a 32-cycle iterative divider for DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU.\\nIncludes start/busy/done handshake, ALTOPS substitutions under\\n`RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS`, and exact RV32M corner-case handling.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate MDU, route operands to it, detect cold M-op via opcode\\nencoding, assert `ex_long_busy` while MDU is active, and select MDU\\nresult into EX/MEM when done.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `ex_long_busy` alongside existing `dmem_ready` / `imem_ready`\\nstall sources. Treat MDU busy like a dmem stall: freeze IF/ID/EX\\nand bubble EX/MEM until the unit completes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `ex_long_busy` signal from ex_stage into hazard_unit.\\nNo top-level IO changes.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T10:45:00.160423Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 1}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r2s0\", \"title\": \"Pre-compute branch target and pc+4 in earlier stages\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The EX stage currently computes two 32-bit additions on its critical path:\\nbranch_target = pc + imm (for branches and JAL) and pc + 4 (for JAL/JALR\\nreturn address and pc_next on not-taken paths). These adders sit between\\nthe ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\\nfrom branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\\nthese values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\\npipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\\ncloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\\nFmax seeds without any IPC change.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage currently computes two 32-bit additions on its critical path:\\nbranch_target = pc + imm (for branches and JAL) and pc + 4 (for JAL/JALR\\nreturn address and pc_next on not-taken paths). These adders sit between\\nthe ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\\nfrom branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\\nthese values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\\npipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\\ncloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\\nFmax seeds without any IPC change.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t, and add branch_target to id_ex_t.\\nIn if_stage, compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 4. In id_stage, compute\\nbranch_target = in.pc + imm and capture both pc_plus4 and branch_target\\ninto the ID/EX register. In ex_stage, replace every occurrence of\\nin.pc + 4 with in.pc_plus4 and every occurrence of in.pc + in.imm with\\nin.branch_target. This removes the pc+4 and pc+imm adders from EX,\\nleaving only the JALR rs1+imm adder and the ALU itself.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 289.97, \"delta_pct\": -8.01, \"vs_baseline\": 2.53, \"fmax_mhz\": 130.24, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9475, \"ff\": 1933, \"seeds\": [127.37, 133.0, 130.24], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:09:45.983278Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r2s0 (regression, -8.01%): Pre-computing pc+4 in IF and pc+imm in ID to remove adders from EX backfires because the adders were previously hidden in parallel with the ALU's longer delay; moving them upstream creates new critical paths in lighter stages and worsens overall Fmax.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Find hypotheses with low LUT4","truncated":false},"title":"Find hypotheses with low LUT4","time":{"start":1778780639731,"end":1778780639733}},"id":"prt_e27968d660019uPsRvF7C2Okrl","sessionID":"ses_1d8755284ffenbzd0kSUkbHYpg","messageID":"msg_e27967148001dw9N5ort3fcyEu"}}
