the existing `forward_unit` already asserts select `2'd1` whenever\\nthe EX/MEM instruction writes the matching `rd`, the EX-stage operand mux\\nwill automatically pick up the actual load data instead of the memory\\naddress.  Finally, remove the `load_use_hazard` logic from `hazard_unit`\\n(and its now-unused inputs `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2`) so the pipeline no longer inserts a bubble for this case.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it the\\ninternal `load_data` value (the shifted/sign-extended load result\\ncomputed combinationally from `dmem_rdata`). No other logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"1. Create a new top-level wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` and connect\\n   it to `u_mem.load_data_out`.\\n2. Change the `.fwd_ex_mem` port connection into `u_ex` from\\n   `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n3. Update the `hazard_unit` instantiation to remove the four now-unused\\n   ports: `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, `if_id_rs2`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the `load_use_hazard` combinational block entirely. The stall and\\nflush equations should no longer include `load_use_hazard`:\\n  `stall_if = imem_stall || dmem_stall;`\\n  `stall_id = dmem_stall;`\\n  `flush_id = redirect && !dmem_stall;`\\nRemove the input ports `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2` since they are no longer referenced.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it the\\ninternal `load_data` value (the shifted/sign-extended load result\\ncomputed combinationally from `dmem_rdata`). No other logic changes.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"1. Create a new top-level wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` and connect\\n   it to `u_mem.load_data_out`.\\n2. Change the `.fwd_ex_mem` port connection into `u_ex` from\\n   `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n3. Update the `hazard_unit` instantiation to remove the four now-unused\\n   ports: `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, `if_id_rs2`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the `load_use_hazard` combinational block entirely. The stall and\\nflush equations should no longer include `load_use_hazard`:\\n  `stall_if = imem_stall || dmem_stall;`\\n  `stall_id = dmem_stall;`\\n  `flush_id = redirect && !dmem_stall;`\\nRemove the input ports `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2` since they are no longer referenced.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 315.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 11.46, \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10217, \"ff\": 1864, \"seeds\": [146.07, 134.99, 141.58], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:51:56.070027Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 3, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r3s1\", \"title\": \"Eliminate load-use stall with MEM-to-EX forwarding\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls ID by one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard (a LOAD in EX followed by an instruction in ID that reads the\\nLOAD's rd).  CoreMark's pointer-chasing, list-walk, and matrix-access\\npatterns contain a high density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops,\\nso this bubble is a significant IPC limiter.  Branch-related structural\\nchanges have already been exhausted with neutral or negative results;\\nthe data-forwarding network is the remaining untouched structural knob.\\nBy forwarding the sign/zero-extended load data directly from the\\ncombinational MEM-stage output to the EX-stage operand muxes, the\\ndependent instruction can enter EX in the cycle immediately after the\\nLOAD moves to MEM, eliminating the stall entirely.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls ID by one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard (a LOAD in EX followed by an instruction in ID that reads the\\nLOAD's rd).  CoreMark's pointer-chasing, list-walk, and matrix-access\\npatterns contain a high density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops,\\nso this bubble is a significant IPC limiter.  Branch-related structural\\nchanges have already been exhausted with neutral or negative results;\\nthe data-forwarding network is the remaining untouched structural knob.\\nBy forwarding the sign/zero-extended load data directly from the\\ncombinational MEM-stage output to the EX-stage operand muxes, the\\ndependent instruction can enter EX in the cycle immediately after the\\nLOAD moves to MEM, eliminating the stall entirely.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard stall from the hazard unit and add a new\\nforwarding source from the MEM-stage load_data output to the EX-stage\\noperand muxes.\\n\\n1. In mem_stage.sv, expose the combinational load_data signal as an\\n   output port (fwd_load_data).\\n2. In forward_unit.sv, add a third forwarding priority:\\n   when the instruction in EX/MEM is a load (ex_mem_ctrl.mem_read) and\\n   its rd matches id_ex_rs1/rs2 (and rd != 0), assert a new select\\n   code (e.g. 2'b11) that picks fwd_load_data.\\n3. In ex_stage.sv, add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend the rs1/rs2\\n   muxes to select it under the new forwarding code.\\n4. In hazard_unit.sv, strip load_use_hazard out of stall_if, stall_id,\\n   and flush_id.  The remaining stall/flush reasons (imem/dmem stalls\\n   and EX redirects) are unchanged.\\n5. In core.sv, wire the new mem_stage output into ex_stage and\\n   forward_unit.\\n\\nThis keeps the RVFI retirement boundary at MEM/WB and does not alter\\ntrap behaviour, ISA decoding, or the nret=1 top-level port contract.\\nThe only timing risk is a longer combinational path from dmem_rdata\\nthrough the MEM load shifter to the EX ALU, but on the Tang Nano 20K\\nthe BRAM read delay plus byte-shift logic is expected to be comparable\\nto the existing ALU+branch path, so the IPC gain should dominate.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose combinational load_data as output port fwd_load_data.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add third forwarding priority for MEM-stage load data (ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_rd match).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire new fwd_load_data port and forwarding selects between mem_stage, forward_unit, and ex_stage.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose combinational load_data as output port fwd_load_data.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add third forwarding priority for MEM-stage load data (ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_rd match).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire new fwd_load_data port and forwarding selects between mem_stage, forward_un