un log: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1/formal/last_run-84805.log\\nPer-check logs in: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1/formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench-84805/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 7, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\", \"title\": \"Split ALU into fast and M-extension paths with final 2:1 mux\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure rtl/alu.sv so that:\\n1. A \\\"fast\\\" always_comb block computes ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SLT,\\n   SLTU, SLL, SRL, SRA, and LUI into a local `fast_out` variable.\\n2. A separate \\\"muldiv\\\" always_comb block (guarded by the existing\\n   opcode if-gate) computes the 64-bit products and DIV/REM results\\n   into a local `m_out` variable.\\n3. A final assignment `out = (op >= ALU_MUL) ? m_out : fast_out;`\\n   drives the output through a single 2:1 mux instead of a 19:1 case\\n   statement.  This keeps the ALTOPS branch intact and does not change\\n   any bit-level results.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 396.13, \"delta_pct\": 18.48, \"vs_baseline\": 40.06, \"fmax_mhz\": 165.51, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4178194, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9927, \"ff\": 1874, \"seeds\": [153.54, 165.51, 166.97], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T15:52:25.889516Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 8, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r8s0 (improvement, +18.48%): Opcode gating alone does not fully remove multiplier/divider inputs from the fast-path mux tree when heavy and light ops share a large case statement; explicitly splitting the ALU into fast and M-extension paths with a final 2:1 mux is required to truly shorten the critical path for base integer ops.\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nalyzed by the STA tool even when\\nthe current instruction is not a divide, keeping the divider on the\\ncritical path for ADD/SHIFT/LOGIC operations. CoreMark rarely (if ever)\\nuses division, so any IPC impact is negligible.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Introduce intermediate variables (div_result, divu_result, rem_result,\\nremu_result) and guard their computation with the same if-gate pattern\\nalready used for multiplies: only evaluate the `/` and `%` operators\\nwhen op is ALU_DIV/ALU_DIVU/ALU_REM/ALU_REMU.  The case statement then\\nselects the pre-computed variables.  This physically disconnects the\\ndivider inputs for non-DIV instructions, shortening the worst-case\\ncombinational path and raising Fmax with no architectural change.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Add div_result/divu_result/rem_result/remu_result variables,\\nconditionally compute them inside an opcode-guarded if block,\\nand reference those variables in the case statement instead of\\ninline / and % operators.  Keep the ALTOPS branch unchanged.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Add div_result/divu_result/rem_result/remu_result variables,\\nconditionally compute them inside an opcode-guarded if block,\\nand reference those variables in the case statement instead of\\ninline / and % operators.  Keep the ALTOPS branch unchanged.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 296.34, \"delta_pct\": -5.99, \"vs_baseline\": 4.78, \"fmax_mhz\": 133.1, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9809, \"ff\": 1863, \"seeds\": [133.1, 129.57, 134.39], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"# Implementation Notes \\u2014 Gate Divider Evaluation by Opcode in ALU\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\nEdited `cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv` only:\\n\\n1. Added four intermediate `logic [31:0]` variables: `div_result`, `divu_result`, `rem_result`, `remu_result`.\\n2. Placed their computation inside an opcode-guarded `if` block that only evaluates when `op` is `ALU_DIV`, `ALU_DIVU`, `ALU_REM`, or `ALU_REMU`.  The block defaults all four results to `32'b0` when the guard is false, mirroring the existing multiply-gating pattern (`mul_ss`/`mul_uu`/`mul_su`).\\n3. Replaced the inline `/` and `%` operators in the non-ALTOPS `case` items with references to the pre-computed variables:\\n   - `ALU_DIV`  \\u2192 `div_result`\\n   - `ALU_DIVU` \\u2192 `divu_result`\\n   - `ALU_REM`  \\u2192 `rem_result`\\n   - `ALU_REMU` \\u2192 `remu_result`\\n4. Left the `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch untouched (it uses XOR-of-add/sub stand-ins and has no real divider logic).\\n\\n## Deviations\\n\\nNone. The change follows the proposed hypothesis exactly.\\n\\n## Concerns\\n\\nNone. The semantics of every divide/remainder edge case (divide-by-zero, `INT_MIN/-1` overflow) are preserved bit-for-bit with the original inline expressions. The only effect is physical: the divider inputs are disconnected from the combinational path when the ALU opcode is not a divide/remainder, which should shorten the critical path for ADD/SHIFT/LOGIC operations and raise Fmax on inference targets.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- **Verilator lint**: `verilator --lint-only -Wall -Wno-MULTITOP -sv +incdir+cores/bench/rtl cores/bench/rtl/*.sv` \\u2014 clean, no warnings/errors.\\n- **Local formal**: `RTL_DIR=cores/bench/rtl CORE_NAME=bench bash formal/run_all.sh` \\u2014 **53 passed, 0 failed** (auto-detected `nret=1`, used `wrapper_si.sv` + `checks_si.cfg`).\\n\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T13:37:05.685313Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 5, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r5s0 (regression, -5.99%): Explicit opcode gating of divide/remainder operations regressed Fmax because FPGA synthesis tools already optimize case-statement divider inference, and the added opcode-comparison and pre-compute mux logic added combinational delay that outweighed any path reduction; timing micro-optimizations that work for multiplies do not automatically transfer to dividers.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r6s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 6, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in two places (JAL return address and fall-through\\npc_next) and uses a full 32-bit pc+imm adder for misalignment checks that feed\\nthe redirect signal back to IF. On FPGA this adds combinational delay to the\\ncritical path. Since IF already computes pc+4 for next_pc, and RV32I guarantees\\npc[1:0]=0 and branch/jump immediate[0]=0, we can eliminate adders from the\\nredirect/misalign path without changing semantics.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"1. Pre-compute pc+4 in if_stage and pass it through if_id_t and id_ex_t so\\n   ex_stage uses the pipelined value instead of recomputing pc+4.\\n2. Simplify branch and JAL misalignment checks to use in.imm[1] instead of\\n   (pc+imm)[1:0], removing the pc+imm adder from the misalign_fault path.\\n3. Collapse the EX/MEM pc_next mux to `redirect ? redirect_target : pc_plus_4`,\\n   which is equivalent because `redirect` already incorporates `!misalign_fault`.\\n4. Remove the unused `branch_target` field from ex_mem_t to save 32 FFs and\\n   reduce routing.\\nThese changes shorten the EX->IF redirect critical path and reduce EX\\ncombinational logic, raising Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `pc_plus_4` to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t`. Remove unused `branch_target` from `ex_mem_t`.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Drive `out.pc_plus_4 = pc + 32'd4` in the combinational IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Capture `in.pc_plus_4` into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use `in.pc_plus_4` for JAL return address and pc_next fall-through. Simplify misalign checks: branches/JAL use `in.imm[1]`; JALR uses `jalr_sum[1]`. Collapse pc_next to `redirect ? redirect_target : in.pc_plus_4`. Remove `branch_target` assignment.\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r6s1\", \"title\": \"Forward exact load_data from MEM to EX to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The 5-stage pipeline currently stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard.\\nCoreMark contains frequent pointer-chasing and array indexing patterns that\\ntrigger these stalls. Previous attempts failed because the forwarded value\\ndid not exactly match the WB write value. mem_stage already computes the\\nfully byte-aligned and sign-extended load_data combinationally; exposing it\\nto the EX-stage forward mux allows us to remove the stall entirely without\\nduplicating extraction logic.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The 5-stage pipeline currently stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard.\\nCoreMark contains frequent pointer-chasing and array indexing patterns that\\ntrigger these stalls. Previous attempts failed because the forwarded value\\ndid not exactly match the WB write value. mem_stage already computes the\\nfully byte-aligned and sign-extended load_data combinationally; exposing it\\nto the EX-stage forward mux allows us to remove the stall entirely without\\nduplicating extraction logic.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational load_data output to mem_stage and use it in core.sv to\\ndrive the fwd_ex_mem input to ex_stage whenever the instruction in EX/MEM\\nis a LOAD (ctrl.mem_read). Remove the load_use_hazard detection from\\nhazard_unit so that a dependent instruction can enter EX in the same cycle\\nthe LOAD is in MEM. This reuses the existing forward_unit encoding\\n(fwd_rs1_sel/fwd_rs2_sel = 2'b01) and requires no changes to ex_stage or\\nforward_unit.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the internal combinational load_data signal as an additional output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Mux fwd_ex_mem between ex_mem_w.alu_result and mem_stage.load_data based on ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id logic.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the internal combinational load_data signal as an additional output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Mux fwd_ex_mem between ex_mem_w.alu_result and mem_stage.load_data based on ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id logic.\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\n engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] engine_0: S