/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 6, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r7s0\", \"title\": \"Forward exact load_data from MEM to EX to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"Load-use stalls are the primary IPC bottleneck in the 5-stage baseline.\\nA LOAD followed by a dependent ALU instruction currently stalls for one\\ncycle.  Previous MEM-to-EX forwarding attempts failed because they\\nforwarded raw dmem_rdata (wrong for byte/halfword loads) or added\\nunused ports to forward_unit (compile failure).  By replicating the\\nfull mem_stage byte-alignment and sign-extension logic in the\\ntop-level forwarding path, the forwarded value matches the WB write\\nvalue exactly, satisfying RVFI.  Re-using the existing forward_unit\\nencoding (EX_MEM=2'd1) avoids port changes.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Load-use stalls are the primary IPC bottleneck in the 5-stage baseline.\\nA LOAD followed by a dependent ALU instruction currently stalls for one\\ncycle.  Previous MEM-to-EX forwarding attempts failed because they\\nforwarded raw dmem_rdata (wrong for byte/halfword loads) or added\\nunused ports to forward_unit (compile failure).  By replicating the\\nfull mem_stage byte-alignment and sign-extension logic in the\\ntop-level forwarding path, the forwarded value matches the WB write\\nvalue exactly, satisfying RVFI.  Re-using the existing forward_unit\\nencoding (EX_MEM=2'd1) avoids port changes.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"In core.sv, replicate mem_stage's load_data computation\\ncombinationally and drive it onto fwd_ex_mem whenever EX/MEM holds a\\nload (mem_read=1).  This lets the existing forward_unit and ex_stage\\nmuxes route the loaded value to a dependent instruction in EX,\\neliminating the one-cycle load-use stall for all load widths.  In\\nhazard_unit.sv, clear load_use_hazard so the pipeline no longer\\nstalls on any load-use.  During a dmem stall the pipeline still\\nfreezes via dmem_stall, so the forwarding path is only active when\\ndmem_rdata is valid.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Replicate mem_stage load_data extraction and sign-extension; mux it onto fwd_ex_mem when EX/MEM.ctrl.mem_read is set, otherwise pass ex_mem_w.alu_result as before.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Set load_use_hazard = 1'b0 unconditionally; MEM-to-EX forwarding now covers the case that the old stall protected.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Replicate mem_stage load_data extraction and sign-extension; mux it onto fwd_ex_mem when EX/MEM.ctrl.mem_read is set, otherwise pass ex_mem_w.alu_result as before.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Set load_use_hazard = 1'b0 unconditionally; MEM-to-EX forwarding now covers the case that the old stall protected.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 334.35, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 18.22, \"fmax_mhz\": 139.7, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4178194, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9980, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [139.7, 149.25, 136.74], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T14:55:52.273075Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 7, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/decoder.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/test/test_decoder.py', 'cores/bench/test/test_pipeline.py', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_ex_stage.sv']\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r7s1\", \"title\": \"Merge ID and EX into single 4-stage pipeline\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline pays a 2-cycle penalty for every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because branch resolution happens in EX, flushing IF and ID.\\nCoreMark has a significant fraction of control-flow instructions; collapsing ID\\nand EX into one combinational stage cuts the mispredict/jump penalty to 1 cycle.\\nIn addition, by exposing the MEM stage's extracted load_data as a forward source,\\nload-use hazards can be resolved via forwarding rather than stall, eliminating the\\n1-cycle load-use bubble entirely.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline pays a 2-cycle penalty for every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because branch resolution happens in EX, flushing IF and ID.\\nCoreMark has a significant fraction of control-flow instructions; collapsing ID\\nand EX into one combinational stage cuts the mispredict/jump penalty to 1 cycle.\\nIn addition, by exposing the MEM stage's extracted load_data as a forward source,\\nload-use hazards can be resolved via forwarding rather than stall, eliminating the\\n1-cycle load-use bubble entirely.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure the pipeline from IF-ID-EX-MEM-WB (5 stages) to IF-ID/EX-MEM-WB\\n(4 stages).  A new id_ex_stage module performs decode, regfile read, immediate\\ngeneration, operand forwarding, ALU execution, and branch resolution all in one\\ncombinational cloud, capturing results in a single pipeline register that feeds\\nMEM.  The mem_stage gains a combinational forward_data output (mem_to_reg ?\\nload_data : alu_result) so the forward_unit can source the freshest register\\nvalue from the MEM stage itself, removing the need for load-use stalls.\\nhazard_unit is simplified: load_use detection is removed, dmem stalls freeze the\\nID/EX register and bubble IF as before, and redirects kill only the single\\ninstruction in flight behind the branch.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/id_ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"New merged stage replacing id_stage and ex_stage. Combinational decode, regfile read, imm_gen, operand forwarding (from MEM stage and MEM/WB), ALU, branch/jump resolve, and misalign trap. Single registered output (ex_mem_t) feeding MEM stage. JAL/JALR/BNE/etc. resolved here.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Rewire 4-stage topology (IF -> ID/EX -> MEM -> WB). Connect mem_stage forward_data to the EX operand muxes. Remove id_stage and ex_stage instances, instantiate id_ex_stage. Adjust hazard/forward wiring.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard and associated stall/flush logic. In 4-stage with MEM forwarding, load-use is handled by the forward path. Keep imem/dmem stall and redirect flush logic, adapted so redirect only flushes IF and bubbles the single ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational forward_data output that exposes the value that will be written to the register file (load_data for LOADs, alu_result otherwise). This lets the ID/EX stage forward the MEM-stage result combinationally, eliminating load-use stalls.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change; the existing 2-bit select encoding (01 = stage ahead, 10 = stage two ahead) is reused. The data source for the 01 select is now mem_stage.forward_data instead of ex_mem_w.alu_result.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/id_ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"New merged stage replacing id_stage and ex_stage. Combinational decode, regfile read, imm_gen, operand forwarding (from MEM stage and MEM/WB), ALU, branch/jump resolve, and misalign trap. Single registered output (ex_mem_t) feeding MEM stage. JAL/JALR/BNE/etc. resolved here.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Rewire 4-stage topology (IF -> ID/EX -> MEM -> WB). Connect mem_stage forward_data to the EX operand muxes. Remove id_stage and ex_stage instances, instantiate id_ex_stage. Adjust hazard/forward wiring.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard and associated stall/flush logic. In 4-stage with MEM forwarding, load-use is handled by the forward path. Keep imem/dmem stall and redirect flush logic, adapted so redirect only flushes IF and bubbles the single ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational forward_data output that exposes the value that will be written to the register file (load_data for LOADs, alu_result otherwise). This lets the ID/EX stage forward the MEM-stage result combinationally, eliminating load-use stalls.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"No functional change; the existing 2-bit select encoding (01 = stage ahead, 10 = stage two ahead) is reused. The data source for the 01 select is now mem_stage.forward_data instead of ex_mem_w.alu_result.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\nshed (returncode=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:03 (3)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:02  Status: passed\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock ti