{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778756422766,"sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a7e1ffeJXQUJnNQ0qh607","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r2s0\ntitle: Pre-compute branch target and pc+4 in earlier stages\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage currently computes two 32-bit additions on its critical path:\n  branch_target = pc + imm (for branches and JAL) and pc + 4 (for JAL/JALR\n  return address and pc_next on not-taken paths). These adders sit between\n  the ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\n  from branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\n  these values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\n  pipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\n  cloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\n  Fmax seeds without any IPC change.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t, and add branch_target to id_ex_t.\n  In if_stage, compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 4. In id_stage, compute\n  branch_target = in.pc + imm and capture both pc_plus4 and branch_target\n  into the ID/EX register. In ex_stage, replace every occurrence of\n  in.pc + 4 with in.pc_plus4 and every occurrence of in.pc + in.imm with\n  in.branch_target. This removes the pc+4 and pc+imm adders from EX,\n  leaving only the JALR rs1+imm adder and the ALU itself.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both\n      in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with\n      in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r2s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r2s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778756422762,"end":1778756422765}},"id":"prt_e2624eafd007Dvf9ft0psa6Wz7","sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a7e1ffeJXQUJnNQ0qh607","messageID":"msg_e2624bced001l9m1o9Lv5vSqH5"}}
