g.sv\n27:     description: Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\n28:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n29:     description: Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\n30:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n31:     description: Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both\n32:       in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\n33:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n34:     description: Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with\n35:       in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r2s0\ntitle: Pre-compute branch target and pc+4 in earlier stages\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage currently computes two 32-bit additions on its critical path:\n  branch_target = pc + imm (for branches and JAL) and pc + 4 (for JAL/JALR\n  return address and pc_next on not-taken paths). These adders sit between\n  the ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\n  from branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\n  these values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\n  pipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\n  cloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\n  Fmax seeds without any IPC change.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t, and add branch_target to id_ex_t.\n  In if_stage, compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 4. In id_stage, compute\n  branch_target = in.pc + imm and capture both pc_plus4 and branch_target\n  into the ID/EX register. In ex_stage, replace every occurrence of\n  in.pc + 4 with in.pc_plus4 and every occurrence of in.pc + in.imm with\n  in.branch_target. This removes the pc+4 and pc+imm adders from EX,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r2s0.yaml","ti