{"type":"text","timestamp":1778756451280,"sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a7e1ffeJXQUJnNQ0qh607","part":{"id":"prt_e2625667b002nR2cYbwt55BN9F","messageID":"msg_e26254685001G4CCXO4CswhdlA","sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a7e1ffeJXQUJnNQ0qh607","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis YAML written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r2s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** The hypothesis proposes a **micro-optimization** that pre-computes `pc+4` in the IF stage and `branch_target = pc+imm` in the ID stage, carrying both values through pipeline registers. This removes two 32-bit adders from the EX-stage combinational path (where branch resolution and redirect generation happen), shortening the critical path back to the PC register and improving worst-case Fmax seeds without any IPC penalty.","time":{"start":1778756445819,"end":1778756451279}}}
