 the fast-path case items (ADD, SUB, logic,\\nshifts, etc.), shortening the critical path and raising Fmax.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Guard the 64-bit multiply computations inside a conditional case block so they only execute for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU ops. Default the product variables to zero so the main output case statement remains unchanged.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n        {\n            \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n            \"description\": \"Guard the 64-bit multiply computations inside a conditional case block so they only execute for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU ops. Default the product variables to zero so the main output case statement remains unchanged.\\n\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n    \"fitness\": 315.22,\n    \"delta_pct\": 11.46,\n    \"vs_baseline\": 11.46,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58,\n    \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n    \"cycles\": 4491485,\n    \"iterations\": 10,\n    \"lut4\": 10217,\n    \"ff\": 1864,\n    \"seeds\": [\n        146.07,\n        134.99,\n        141.58\n    ],\n    \"formal_passed\": true,\n    \"cosim_passed\": true,\n    \"error\": null,\n    \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T10:24:34.709300Z\",\n    \"slot\": 0,\n    \"round_id\": 1,\n    \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r1s0 (improvement, +11.46%): On inference FPGA targets, unconditionally computing wide multiply products inside the ALU keeps multiplier hardware on the combinational critical path for non-M opcodes; gating the multiply evaluation by opcode removes it from the fast path and raises Fmax with no IPC penalty.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n    \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r1s0\",\n    \"title\": \"Guard ALU multipliers off critical path for non-M ops\",\n    \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline ALU unconditionally computes three 64-bit products on every\\ncycle, even for simple ADD/SUB/AND/OR/XOR/SLT/SLTU/SLL/SRL/SRA/LUI\\noperations. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-18C) these inferred multipliers\\nsit on the combinational critical path and limit Fmax. CoreMark is\\ndominated by integer ALU and memory ops, so the multiplier is almost\\nnever exercised, yet it still degrades timing for every other operation.\\nRemoving it from the critical path should raise Fmax with zero IPC risk.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": {\n        \"motivation\": \"The baseline ALU unconditionally computes three 64-bit products on every\\ncycle, even for simple ADD/SUB/AND/OR/XOR/SLT/SLTU/SLL/SRL/SRA/LUI\\noperations. On the Tang Nano 20K (GW2AR-18C) these inferred multipliers\\nsit on the combinational critical path and limit Fmax. CoreMark is\\ndominated by integer ALU and memory ops, so the multiplier is almost\\nnever exercised, yet it still degrades timing for every other operation.\\nRemoving it from the critical path should raise Fmax with zero IPC risk.\\n\",\n        \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure alu.sv so the 64-bit multiply assignments (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su) are only evaluated when the ALU operation is MUL, MULH, MULHU,\\nor MULHSU. For all other opcodes the products are tied to zero inside\\nthe always_comb block. This tells the synthesis tool that the multiplier\\nhardware is not needed on the fast-path case items (ADD, SUB, logic,\\nshifts, etc.), shortening the critical path and raising Fmax.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Guard the 64-bit multiply computations inside a conditional case block so they only execute for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU ops. Default the product variables to zero so the main output case statement remains unchanged.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n        {\n            \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n            \"description\": \"Guard the 64-bit multiply computations inside a conditional case block so they only execute for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU ops. Default the product variables to zero so the main output case statement remains unchanged.\\n\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n    \"fitness\": 315.22,\n    \"delta_pct\": 11.46,\n    \"vs_baseline\": 11.46,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58,\n    \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n    \"cycles\": 4491485,\n    \"iterations\": 10,\n    \"lut4\": 10217,\n    \"ff\": 1864,\n    \"seeds\": [\n        146.07,\n        134.99,\n        141.58\n    ],\n    \"formal_passed\": true,\n    \"cosim_passed\": true,\n    \"error\": null,\n    \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T10:24:34.709300Z\",\n    \"slot\": 0,\n    \"round_id\": 1,\n    \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r1s0 (improvement, +11.46%): On inference FPGA targets, unconditionally computing wide multiply products inside the ALU keeps multiplier hardware on the combinational critical path for non-M opcodes; gating the multiply evaluation by opcode removes it from the fast path and raises Fmax with no IPC penalty.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Extract full JSON for best experiment","truncated":false},"title":"Extract full JSON for best experiment","time":{"start":1778757990519,"end":1778757990522}},"id":"prt_e263cf358002EnDEgnATXvsv8D","sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c473ffehCqw6PNuqEWnLH","messageID":"msg_e263ce1fd001peUv64Vjp1oy3O"}}
