{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778758504419,"sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c473ffehCqw6PNuqEWnLH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r3s0\ntitle: MEM-stage load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\n  because the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\n  CoreMark is pointer- and array-heavy, so these stalls are frequent.\n  By forwarding the combinational load data directly from the MEM stage to\n  the EX-stage operand muxes, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\n  very next cycle without any bubble, directly improving IPC.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a combinational `load_data_out` port to `mem_stage` that exposes the\n  internally computed, shifted/sign-extended load result. In `core.sv`, change\n  the `fwd_ex_mem` connection fed into `ex_stage` from a plain\n  `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to the multiplexed value\n  `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\n  Because the existing `forward_unit` already asserts select `2'd1` whenever\n  the EX/MEM instruction writes the matching `rd`, the EX-stage operand mux\n  will automatically pick up the actual load data instead of the memory\n  address.  Finally, remove the `load_use_hazard` logic from `hazard_unit`\n  (and its now-unused inputs `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\n  `if_id_rs2`) so the pipeline no longer inserts a bubble for this case.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it the\n      internal `load_data` value (the shifted/sign-extended load result\n      computed combinationally from `dmem_rdata`). No other logic changes.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      1. Create a new top-level wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` and connect\n         it to `u_mem.load_data_out`.\n      2. Change the `.fwd_ex_mem` port connection into `u_ex` from\n         `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\n         `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\n      3. Update the `hazard_unit` instantiation to remove the four now-unused\n         ports: `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, `if_id_rs2`.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Remove the `load_use_hazard` combinational block entirely. The stall and\n      flush equations should no longer include `load_use_hazard`:\n        `stall_if = imem_stall || dmem_stall;`\n        `stall_id = dmem_stall;`\n        `flush_id = redirect && !dmem_stall;`\n      Remove the input ports `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\n      `if_id_rs2` since they are no longer referenced.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r3s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r3s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778758504406,"end":1778758504418}},"id":"prt_e26449cbf004N8fFPB5CXqaekV","sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c473ffehCqw6PNuqEWnLH","messageID":"msg_e26447fd90011X19cFuOBJZQg6"}}
