{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778765202709,"sessionID":"ses_1d95e7e3effeGlqoD6ellv5tdO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r5s0\ntitle: Gate divider evaluation by opcode in ALU\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The ALU currently gates 64-bit multiply product evaluation behind an\n  opcode check, which was proven in a prior iteration to raise Fmax by\n  removing the multiplier from the critical path of non-M instructions.\n  The divide/remainder operations (DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU) are still computed\n  inside the case statement without an explicit input gate. On FPGA\n  inference targets the divider is a large combinational cell whose\n  physical path from a/b to out is analyzed by the STA tool even when\n  the current instruction is not a divide, keeping the divider on the\n  critical path for ADD/SHIFT/LOGIC operations. CoreMark rarely (if ever)\n  uses division, so any IPC impact is negligible.\nhypothesis: |\n  Introduce intermediate variables (div_result, divu_result, rem_result,\n  remu_result) and guard their computation with the same if-gate pattern\n  already used for multiplies: only evaluate the `/` and `%` operators\n  when op is ALU_DIV/ALU_DIVU/ALU_REM/ALU_REMU.  The case statement then\n  selects the pre-computed variables.  This physically disconnects the\n  divider inputs for non-DIV instructions, shortening the worst-case\n  combinational path and raising Fmax with no architectural change.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: |\n      Add div_result/divu_result/rem_result/remu_result variables,\n      conditionally compute them inside an opcode-guarded if block,\n      and reference those variables in the case statement instead of\n      inline / and % operators.  Keep the ALTOPS branch unchanged.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778765202701,"end":1778765202708}},"id":"prt_e26aaf2d0001KHg4RlZKYvF51v","sessionID":"ses_1d95e7e3effeGlqoD6ellv5tdO","messageID":"msg_e26a181fb001q41PfyTshc8CZh"}}
