{"type":"text","timestamp":1778765218220,"sessionID":"ses_1d95e7e3effeGlqoD6ellv5tdO","part":{"id":"prt_e26ab3353001k4BrK0B7vCyQ4W","messageID":"msg_e26ab1c03001OgbhNRGSfOolEk","sessionID":"ses_1d95e7e3effeGlqoD6ellv5tdO","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** This micro-optimization gates the 32-bit divider/remainder evaluation in `alu.sv` behind an opcode check, mirroring the proven multiply-gating pattern from a prior successful iteration. By physically disconnecting the divider inputs for non-DIV instructions, the worst-case combinational path shortens, which should raise Fmax with negligible IPC impact since CoreMark rarely uses division.","time":{"start":1778765214547,"end":1778765218218}}}
