check>/logfile.txt\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/id_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/if_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/btb.sv']\"\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r3s2\",\n  \"title\": \"32-entry direct-mapped BTB in IF stage to eliminate taken-branch bubbles\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches sequentially, paying a 2-cycle bubble for every\\ntaken branch and JAL. A prior static predictor that computed branch targets\\ncombinationally in IF from imem_data (decode -> imm_gen -> adder) slashed\\nFmax by ~40% because that path starts from the off-chip/BRAM instruction\\nword. A Branch Target Buffer (BTB) avoids that path entirely: it is indexed\\ndirectly by the PC register output, so the predicted next PC is just a small\\ndistributed-RAM read with no instruction decode or adder in the critical\\npath. On the Tang Nano 20K a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\\na single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\\nthe branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches sequentially, paying a 2-cycle bubble for every\\ntaken branch and JAL. A prior static predictor that computed branch targets\\ncombinationally in IF from imem_data (decode -> imm_gen -> adder) slashed\\nFmax by ~40% because that path starts from the off-chip/BRAM instruction\\nword. A Branch Target Buffer (BTB) avoids that path entirely: it is indexed\\ndirectly by the PC register output, so the predicted next PC is just a small\\ndistributed-RAM read with no instruction decode or adder in the critical\\npath. On the Tang Nano 20K a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\\na single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\\nthe branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped BTB to the IF stage.\\n- Read: combinational, indexed by pc[6:2], outputs hit and target[31:0].\\n- Write: registered in EX when a conditional branch or JAL is resolved\\n  taken, storing pc[6:2] -> target.\\n- IF stage: next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target : btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4.\\n- Pipeline a predict_taken bit (= btb_hit) through IF/ID and ID/EX.\\n- EX stage: mispredict = (predict_taken != actual_taken). Redirect only on\\n  mispredict; correct BTB hits flow through with zero bubble. JALR is never\\n  predicted (target depends on rs1).\\nCoreMark's inner loops quickly warm the BTB, after which every loop-back\\nbranch costs zero bubbles instead of two. The BTB read path is shorter than\\nthe previous static predictor's imem_data->decode->adder path, so Fmax\\nimpact should be minimal.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/btb.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en, update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken through the pipeline bundles.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/btb.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en, update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken through the pipeline bundles.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 315.22,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 11.46,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4491485,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10217,\n  \"ff\": 1864,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.07,\n    134.99,\n    141.58\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:48:15.113672Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 3\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r4s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Forward exact load result from MEM to EX and remove load-use stall\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls ID for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark's list-walk, matrix-access, and pointer-chasing patterns contain a\\nhigh density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops, so this bubble is a\\nsignificant IPC limiter. Prior attempts either failed to remove the\\naccompanying hazard-unit interlock (producing a no-op) or forwarded raw\\ndmem_rdata without byte-alignment/sign-extension (breaking RVFI reg checks).\\nBy forwarding the fully processed load_data from the MEM-stage combinational\\noutput directly into the existing EX/MEM forward path, and explicitly deleting\\nthe load_use_hazard stall logic, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle with the exact same value that will later be written to the\\nregfile.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls ID for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark's list-walk, matrix-access, and pointer-chasing patterns contain a\\nhigh density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops, so this bubble is a\\nsignificant IPC limiter. Prior attempts either failed to remove the\\naccompanying hazard-unit interlock (producing a no-op) or forwarded raw\\ndmem_rdata without byte-alignment/sign-extension (breaking RVFI reg checks).\\nBy forwarding the fully processed load_data from the MEM-stage combinational\\noutput directly into the existing EX/MEM forward path, and explicitly deleting\\nthe load_use_hazard stall logic, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle with the exact same value that will later be written to the\\nregfile.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"1. In mem_stage.sv, expose the internal combinational `load_data` signal as a\\n   new output port `load_data_out`. This is the same byte-aligned,\\n   sign/zero-extended value that is captured into the MEM/WB register.\\n2. In core.sv, change the `fwd_ex_mem` connection fed into ex_stage from a\\n   plain `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to the multiplexed value\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n   Because the existing forward_unit already asserts select `2'd1` whenever\\n   the EX/MEM instruction writes the matching `rd`, the EX-stage operand mux\\n   will automatically pick up the actual load result instead of the memory\\n   address.\\n3. In hazard_unit.sv, delete the `load_use_hazard` logic entirely. The signal\\n   must be hard-wired to 0 so the pipeline no longer stalls IF/ID on this\\n   case. The remaining stall sources (imem_ready, dmem_ready, redirect) are\\n   untouched.\\n\\nNo new forwarding select encoding is introduced, no EX-stage operand mux\\ngrows beyond its existing 3-way shape, and the forwarded value is bit-exact\\nwith the WB write path, so RVFI reg checks should pass cleanly.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it to the\\ninternal combinational `load_data` signal that is already computed for\\nthe MEM/WB register.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a local wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` connected to\\n`u_mem.load_data_out`. Change the `fwd_ex_mem` port connection on\\n`u_ex` from `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n`ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove all logic that derives `load_use_hazard` from `id_ex_mem_read`,\\n`id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, and `if_id_rs2`. Tie `load_use_hazard` to 0.\\nKeep the port declarations (or remove them and their connections in\\ncore.sv) \\u2014 the minimal change is to keep the ports and simply not use\\nthem inside the combinational block.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it to the\\ninternal combinational `load_data` signal that is already computed for\\nthe MEM/WB register.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a local wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` connected to\\n`u_mem.load_data_out`. Change the `fwd_ex_mem` port connection on\\n`u_ex` from `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n`ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove all logic that derives `load_use_hazard` from `id_ex_mem_read`,\\n`id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, and `if_id_rs2`. Tie `load_use_hazard` to 0.\\nKeep the port declarations (or remove them and their connections in\\ncore.sv) \\u2014 the minimal change is to keep the ports and simply not use\\nthem inside the combinational block.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"implementation_compile_failed: \",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 4,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-002-r4s1 (broken, n/a): MEM-to-EX load forwarding can reuse the existing forward_unit select encoding by muxing the fwd_ex_mem data source in core.sv; adding unused ports to forward_unit caused an implementation compile failure from unconnected inputs.\"\n}\n---\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\ncurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately\\u2014eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational branch/jump prediction to the IF stage and suppress\\nEX-stage redirects when the prediction is correct.\\n\\n1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\\n2. In if_stage, instantiate a small imm_gen (or inline equivalent) to\\n   extract the B/J immediate from imem_data. Detect opcode 1100011\\n   (BRANCH) and 1101111 (JAL). Predict taken for JAL unconditionally,\\n   and for branches when the immediate sign bit is 1 (backward branch).\\n   On a predicted-taken instruction, redirect next_pc to pc+imm instead\\n   of pc+4. This means the sequential fall-through instruction is never\\n   fetched, so no flush is needed on a correct prediction.\\n3. In id_stage, pass predict_taken through the ID/EX register.\\n4. In ex_stage, change the redirect condition so it only fires on a\\n   mispredict: for branches when branch_taken != predict_taken, and for\\n   jumps when predict_taken == 0 (i.e. JALR, which is never predicted).\\n   Correctly predicted JALs and backward branches therefore flow through\\n   the pipeline with zero bubble penalty.\\n\\nThis is a much simpler and lower-risk version of the broken 32-entry\\ndynamic-PHT attempt: no stateful structures, no PHT update logic, and a\\ntiny combinational path (opcode compare \\u2192 imm mux \\u2192 adder) that reuses\\nthe existing pc+4 adder delay budget.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 203.63,\n  \"delta_pct\": -35.4,\n  \"vs_baseline\": -28.0,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 86.74,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10047,\n  \"ff\": 1868,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    86.74,\n    87.03,\n    82.66\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:19:46.077886Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r3s0\",\n  \"title\": \"MEM-stage load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark is pointer- and array-heavy, so these stalls are frequent.\\nBy forwarding the combinational load data directly from the MEM stage to\\nthe EX-stage operand muxes, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle without any bubble, directly improving IPC.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark is pointer- and array-heavy, so these stalls are frequent.\\nBy forwarding the combinational load data directly from the MEM stage to\\nthe EX-stage operand muxes, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle without any bubble, directly improving IPC.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational `load_data_out` port to `mem_stage` that exposes the\\ninternally computed, shifted/sign-extended load result. In `core.sv`, change\\nthe `fwd_ex_mem` connection fed into `ex_stage` from a plain\\n`ex_mem_w.alu_result` to the multiplexed value\\n`ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\nBecause the existing `forward_unit` already asserts select `2'd1` whenever\\nthe EX/MEM instruction writes the matching `rd`, the EX-stage operand mux\\nwill automatically pick up the actual load data instead of the memory\\naddress.  Finally, remove the `load_use_hazard` logic from `hazard_unit`\\n(and its now-unused inputs `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2`) so the pipeline no longer inserts a bubble for this case.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it the\\ninternal `load_data` value (the shifted/sign-extended load result\\ncomputed combinationally from `dmem_rdata`). No other logic changes.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"1. Create a new top-level wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` and connect\\n   it to `u_mem.load_data_out`.\\n2. Change the `.fwd_ex_mem` port connection into `u_ex` from\\n   `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n3. Update the `hazard_unit` instantiation to remove the four now-unused\\n   ports: `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, `if_id_rs2`.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove the `load_use_hazard` combinational block entirely. The stall and\\nflush equations should no longer include `load_use_hazard`:\\n  `stall_if = imem_stall || dmem_stall;`\\n  `stall_id = dmem_stall;`\\n  `flush_id = redirect && !dmem_stall;`\\nRemove the input ports `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2` since they are no longer referenced.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it the\\ninternal `load_data` value (the shifted/sign-extended load result\\ncomputed combinationally from `dmem_rdata`). No other logic changes.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"1. Create a new top-level wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` and connect\\n   it to `u_mem.load_data_out`.\\n2. Change the `.fwd_ex_mem` port connection into `u_ex` from\\n   `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n3. Update the `hazard_unit` instantiation to remove the four now-unused\\n   ports: `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, `if_id_rs2`.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove the `load_use_hazard` combinational block entirely. The stall and\\nflush equations should no longer include `load_use_hazard`:\\n  `stall_if = imem_stall || dmem_stall;`\\n  `stall_id = dmem_stall;`\\n  `flush_id = redirect && !dmem_stall;`\\nRemove the input ports `id_ex_mem_read`, `id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`,\\n`if_id_rs2` since they are no longer referenced.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 315.22,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 11.46,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4491485,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10217,\n  \"ff\": 1864,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.07,\n    134.99,\n    141.58\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:51:56.070027Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r3s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Eliminate load-use stall with MEM-to-EX forwarding\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls ID by one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard (a LOAD in EX followed by an instruction in ID that reads the\\nLOAD's rd).  CoreMark's pointer-chasing, list-walk, and matrix-access\\npatterns contain a high density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops,\\nso this bubble is a significant IPC limiter.  Branch-related structural\\nchanges have already been exhausted with neutral or negative results;\\nthe data-forwarding network is the remaining untouched structural knob.\\nBy forwarding the sign/zero-extended load data directly from the\\ncombinational MEM-stage output to the EX-stage operand muxes, the\\ndependent instruction can enter EX in the cycle immediately after the\\nLOAD moves to MEM, eliminating the stall entirely.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls ID by one cycle on every load-use\\nhazard (a LOAD in EX followed by an instruction in ID that reads the\\nLOAD's rd).  CoreMark's pointer-chasing, list-walk, and matrix-access\\npatterns contain a high density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops,\\nso this bubble is a significant IPC limiter.  Branch-related structural\\nchanges have already been exhausted with neutral or negative results;\\nthe data-forwarding network is the remaining untouched structural knob.\\nBy forwarding the sign/zero-extended load data directly from the\\ncombinational MEM-stage output to the EX-stage operand muxes, the\\ndependent instruction can enter EX in the cycle immediately after the\\nLOAD moves to MEM, eliminating the stall entirely.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard stall from the hazard unit and add a new\\nforwarding source from the MEM-stage load_data output to the EX-stage\\noperand muxes.\\n\\n1. In mem_stage.sv, expose the combinational load_data signal as an\\n   output port (fwd_load_data).\\n2. In forward_unit.sv, add a third forwarding priority:\\n   when the instruction in EX/MEM is a load (ex_mem_ctrl.mem_read) and\\n   its rd matches id_ex_rs1/rs2 (and rd != 0), assert a new select\\n   code (e.g. 2'b11) that picks fwd_load_data.\\n3. In ex_stage.sv, add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend the rs1/rs2\\n   muxes to select it under the new forwarding code.\\n4. In hazard_unit.sv, strip load_use_hazard out of stall_if, stall_id,\\n   and flush_id.  The remaining stall/flush reasons (imem/dmem stalls\\n   and EX redirects) are unchanged.\\n5. In core.sv, wire the new mem_stage output into ex_stage and\\n   forward_unit.\\n\\nThis keeps the RVFI retirement boundary at MEM/WB and does not alter\\ntrap behaviour, ISA decoding, or the nret=1 top-level port contract.\\nThe only timing risk is a longer combinational path from dmem_rdata\\nthrough the MEM load shifter to the EX ALU, but on the Tang Nano 20K\\nthe BRAM read delay plus byte-shift logic is expected to be comparable\\nto the existing ALU+branch path, so the IPC gain should dominate.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 7,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Expose combinational load_data as output port fwd_load_data.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add third forwarding priority for MEM-stage load data (ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_rd match).\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire new fwd_load_data port and forwarding selects between mem_stage, forward_unit, and ex_stage.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 7,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Expose combinational load_data as output port fwd_load_data.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add third forwarding priority for MEM-stage load data (ex_mem_mem_read && ex_mem_rd match).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load_data input and extend rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire new fwd_load_data port and forwarding selects between mem_stage, forward_unit, and ex_stage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\n0/trace.vcd\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:11  Writing trace to Verilog testbench: engine_0/trace_tb.v\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:11  Writing trace to constraints file: engine_0/trace.smtc\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:11  Writing trace to Yosys witness file: engine_0/trace.yw\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:11  Status: failed\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=1)\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: FAIL\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:12 (12)\\nSBY  9:04:25 [reg_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:09 