{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778767475415,"sessionID":"ses_1d93775c5ffebpWHQwJ6cKwaAu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r6s0\ntitle: Pre-compute PC+4 and simplify misalign checks to shorten EX-to-IF redirect path\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in two places (JAL return address and fall-through\n  pc_next) and uses a full 32-bit pc+imm adder for misalignment checks that feed\n  the redirect signal back to IF. On FPGA this adds combinational delay to the\n  critical path. Since IF already computes pc+4 for next_pc, and RV32I guarantees\n  pc[1:0]=0 and branch/jump immediate[0]=0, we can eliminate adders from the\n  redirect/misalign path without changing semantics.\nhypothesis: |\n  1. Pre-compute pc+4 in if_stage and pass it through if_id_t and id_ex_t so\n     ex_stage uses the pipelined value instead of recomputing pc+4.\n  2. Simplify branch and JAL misalignment checks to use in.imm[1] instead of\n     (pc+imm)[1:0], removing the pc+imm adder from the misalign_fault path.\n  3. Collapse the EX/MEM pc_next mux to `redirect ? redirect_target : pc_plus_4`,\n     which is equivalent because `redirect` already incorporates `!misalign_fault`.\n  4. Remove the unused `branch_target` field from ex_mem_t to save 32 FFs and\n     reduce routing.\n  These changes shorten the EX->IF redirect critical path and reduce EX\n  combinational logic, raising Fmax with zero IPC impact.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: >-\n      Add `pc_plus_4` to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t`. Remove unused `branch_target`\n      from `ex_mem_t`.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Drive `out.pc_plus_4 = pc + 32'd4` in the combinational IF/ID bundle.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Capture `in.pc_plus_4` into the ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Use `in.pc_plus_4` for JAL return address and pc_next fall-through.\n      Simplify misalign checks: branches/JAL use `in.imm[1]`; JALR uses\n      `jalr_sum[1]`. Collapse pc_next to `redirect ? redirect_target :\n      in.pc_plus_4`. Remove `branch_target` assignment.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r6s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r6s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r6s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778767475409,"end":1778767475414}},"id":"prt_e26cd82e3001jq4gHrLIZPASle","sessionID":"ses_1d93775c5ffebpWHQwJ6cKwaAu","messageID":"msg_e26cd512e001WwnePFs2i0s2pk"}}
