{"type":"text","timestamp":1778770052836,"sessionID":"ses_1d9115b96ffe8x5ZpDXmUHBSCU","part":{"id":"prt_e26f4ed49003XRndOp0tcGsWW3","messageID":"msg_e26f4bd730013fGBzf1BsVejX4","sessionID":"ses_1d9115b96ffe8x5ZpDXmUHBSCU","type":"text","text":"The hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the proposal:**\n\n* **Angle:** Eliminate load-use stalls by forwarding the exact `load_data` from the MEM stage to EX via the existing `fwd_ex_mem` path.\n* **Key correctness fix vs. prior broken attempts:** Replicate `mem_stage`'s full byte-alignment, shift, and sign-extension logic in `core.sv` so the forwarded value is bit-identical to what WB will eventually write, satisfying `rvfi_reg_check`.\n* **No port changes:** Reuses the existing `forward_unit` `EX_MEM=2'd1` encoding and avoids touching `forward_unit.sv` or `ex_stage.sv` ports.\n* **Expected impact:** ~4% fitness improvement (IPC gain from removing stalls, with minimal Fmax risk).","time":{"start":1778770046281,"end":1778770052835}}}
