{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778776202146,"sessionID":"ses_1d8b3b523ffeL0XdtuYMddy9Z5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\ntitle: \"JAL pre-decode in IF to eliminate unconditional jump bubbles\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  Every JAL currently costs a one-cycle bubble: while JAL travels through ID,\n  the IF stage blindly fetches PC+4; when JAL reaches EX it redirects, flushing\n  the wrongly fetched instruction.  JAL is unconditional and its target is\n  known the moment the instruction is fetched (PC + J-immediate).  Since there\n  is no mispredict possibility for aligned JAL, the IF stage can safely jump\n  immediately, removing the bubble entirely without any prediction state or\n  recovery logic.  This improves IPC for all function calls with no risk of\n  mispredict penalties.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add combinational JAL detection and target computation inside if_stage.sv.\n  When the instruction being emitted to ID is a JAL and its computed target is\n  aligned, override next_pc with the JAL target instead of PC+4.  The PC\n  register updates to the target in the same cycle JAL enters ID, so the\n  pipeline fetches the target instruction one cycle earlier.  In ex_stage.sv,\n  suppress the redirect signal for JAL (keep it only for branches and JALR);\n  because IF already fetched the correct target, there is nothing to flush.\n  Misaligned JAL falls back to PC+4 in IF, preserving the baseline trap-and-\n  fallthrough semantics in EX.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      In the combinational always_comb block that drives out.*, add:\n        1. JAL opcode detection: is_jal = (out.instr[6:0] == 7'b1101111).\n        2. J-immediate extraction from out.instr:\n             jal_imm = {{11{out.instr[31]}}, out.instr[31], out.instr[19:12],\n                        out.instr[20], out.instr[30:21], 1'b0};\n        3. Target adder: jal_target = pc + jal_imm.\n        4. next_pc mux:\n             next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target\n                     : (is_jal && (jal_target[1:0] == 2'b00)) ? jal_target\n                     : pc + 32'd4;\n      Declare is_jal, jal_imm, and jal_target as local logic signals.\n      Do NOT remove or alter the existing I-cache, flush, or stall logic.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Change the redirect assignment so JAL does not assert redirect:\n        assign redirect = (branch_taken || (in.ctrl.is_jump && in.ctrl.is_jalr))\n                          && !misalign_fault;\n      Leave redirect_target, jump_target, branch_target, jalr_sum, and the\n      EX/MEM always_ff block completely unchanged.  JAL still computes\n      pc_next = jump_target and alu_result = pc+4 in the register block as\n      before; the only difference is that EX no longer flushes the pipeline\n      for aligned JAL because IF already redirected.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778776202138,"end":1778776202145}},"id":"prt_e2752b4f5001Wg258C2S7JP2IH","sessionID":"ses_1d8b3b523ffeL0XdtuYMddy9Z5","messageID":"msg_e27521e9e001e4x5qIz5zNeqk0"}}
