{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778780237759,"sessionID":"ses_1d875521dffeRFwpChqm8uVGYC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        obj = json.loads(line)\n        if obj['id'] == 'hyp-20260514-002-r7s1':\n            print(json.dumps(obj, indent=2))\n            break\n\"","description":"Extract hyp-20260514-002-r7s1 full record"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r7s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Merge ID and EX into single 4-stage pipeline\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline pays a 2-cycle penalty for every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because branch resolution happens in EX, flushing IF and ID.\\nCoreMark has a significant fraction of control-flow instructions; collapsing ID\\nand EX into one combinational stage cuts the mispredict/jump penalty to 1 cycle.\\nIn addition, by exposing the MEM stage's extracted load_data as a forward source,\\nload-use hazards can be resolved via forwarding rather than stall, eliminating the\\n1-cycle load-use bubble entirely.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline pays a 2-cycle penalty for every taken branch and\\nunconditional jump because branch resolution happens in EX, flushing IF and ID.\\nCoreMark has a significant fraction of control-flow instructions; collapsing ID\\nand EX into one combinational stage cuts the mispredict/jump penalty to 1 cycle.\\nIn addition, by exposing the MEM stage's extracted load_data as a forward source,\\nload-use hazards can be resolved via forwarding rather than stall, eliminating the\\n1-cycle load-use bubble entirely.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure the pipeline from IF-ID-EX-MEM-WB (5 stages) to IF-ID/EX-MEM-WB\\n(4 stages).  A new id_ex_stage module performs decode, regfile read, immediate\\ngeneration, operand forwarding, ALU execution, and branch resolution all in one\\ncombinational cloud, capturing results in a single pipeline register that feeds\\nMEM.  The mem_stage gains a combinational forward_data output (mem_to_reg ?\\nload_data : alu_result) so the forward_unit can source the freshest register\\nvalue from the MEM stage itself, removing the need for load-use stalls.\\nhazard_unit is simplified: load_use detection is removed, dmem stalls freeze the\\nID/EX register and bubble IF as before, and redirects kill only the single\\ninstruction in flight behind the branch.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"New merged stage replacing id_stage and ex_stage. Combinational decode, regfile read, imm_gen, operand forwarding (from MEM stage and MEM/WB), ALU, branch/jump resolve, and misalign trap. Single registered output (ex_mem_t) feeding MEM stage. JAL/JALR/BNE/etc. resolved here.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Rewire 4-stage topology (IF -> ID/EX -> MEM -> WB). Connect mem_stage forward_data to the EX operand muxes. Remove id_stage and ex_stage instances, instantiate id_ex_stage. Adjust hazard/forward wiring.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard and associated stall/flush logic. In 4-stage with MEM forwarding, load-use is handled by the forward path. Keep imem/dmem stall and redirect flush logic, adapted so redirect only flushes IF and bubbles the single ID/EX register.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational forward_data output that exposes the value that will be written to the register file (load_data for LOADs, alu_result otherwise). This lets the ID/EX stage forward the MEM-stage result combinationally, eliminating load-use stalls.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"No functional change; the existing 2-bit select encoding (01 = stage ahead, 10 = stage two ahead) is reused. The data source for the 01 select is now mem_stage.forward_data instead of ex_mem_w.alu_result.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"New merged stage replacing id_stage and ex_stage. Combinational decode, regfile read, imm_gen, operand forwarding (from MEM stage and MEM/WB), ALU, branch/jump resolve, and misalign trap. Single registered output (ex_mem_t) feeding MEM stage. JAL/JALR/BNE/etc. resolved here.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Rewire 4-stage topology (IF -> ID/EX -> MEM -> WB). Connect mem_stage forward_data to the EX operand muxes. Remove id_stage and ex_stage instances, instantiate id_ex_stage. Adjust hazard/forward wiring.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard and associated stall/flush logic. In 4-stage with MEM forwarding, load-use is handled by the forward path. Keep imem/dmem stall and redirect flush logic, adapted so redirect only flushes IF and bubbles the single ID/EX register.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational forward_data output that exposes the value that will be written to the register file (load_data for LOADs, alu_result otherwise). This lets the ID/EX stage forward the MEM-stage result combinationally, eliminating load-use stalls.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"No functional change; the existing 2-bit select encoding (01 = stage ahead, 10 = stage two ahead) is reused. The data source for the 01 select is now mem_stage.forward_data instead of ex_mem_w.alu_result.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\nshed (returncode=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:03 (3)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_srai_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:02  Status: passed\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:03 (3)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 12:17:50 [insn_sub_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\n\\nFormal: 52 passed, 1 failed\\nFailed: reg_ch0\\n\\n--- reg_ch0/logfile.txt (last 30 lines) ---\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 9..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 10..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 11..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 12..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 13..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 14..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 15..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 16..\\nSBY 12:17:34 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 17..\\nS