{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778780525760,"sessionID":"ses_1d875521dffeRFwpChqm8uVGYC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r11s1\ntitle: Collapse three ALU multipliers into one with correction subtractors\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline ALU computes three independent 64-bit products (signed*signed,\n  unsigned*unsigned, signed*unsigned) on every M-extension opcode, even though\n  all four RV32M multiply results (MUL, MULH, MULHU, MULHSU) can be derived\n  from a single unsigned 64-bit product with cheap 32-bit corrections.\n  At 9927 LUT4 the design is at 99 % of the target; removing two redundant\n  multipliers frees ~1500-2000 LUT4/DSPs, relieving routing congestion and\n  shortening the M-path combinational delay with zero IPC impact.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace mul_ss and mul_su with mathematical corrections to mul_uu.\n  - MUL    = mul_uu[31:0] (unchanged)\n  - MULHU  = mul_uu[63:32] (unchanged)\n  - MULHSU = mul_uu[63:32] - (a[31] ? b : 0)\n  - MULH   = mul_uu[63:32] - (a[31] ? b : 0) - (b[31] ? a : 0)\n  The 32-bit unsigned subtractions wrap modulo 2^32, which is exactly the\n  high-half behavior required by RV32M two's-complement semantics.\n  Verified by exhaustive edge-case testing and 10,000 random vectors.\n  The ALTOPS formal branch and the divider path are left untouched.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: |\n      1. Remove `mul_ss` and `mul_su` variables and their assignments.\n      2. Keep only `mul_uu = {32'b0, a} * {32'b0, b}` inside the multiply\n         guard block.\n      3. Pre-compute correction terms:\n           `corr_a = a[31] ? b : 0;`\n           `corr_b = b[31] ? a : 0;`\n      4. In the non-ALTOPS case statement, replace:\n           ALU_MULH:   m_out = mul_uu[63:32] - corr_a - corr_b;\n           ALU_MULHSU: m_out = mul_uu[63:32] - corr_a;\n           (ALU_MUL and ALU_MULHU stay unchanged).\n      5. The fast-path 2:1 mux and the ALTOPS branch must remain unchanged.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778780525752,"end":1778780525759}},"id":"prt_e27949b80001jmW6kqnFNoc96G","sessionID":"ses_1d875521dffeRFwpChqm8uVGYC","messageID":"msg_e279391490012n1vQ4ccOHUW9H"}}
