{"type":"text","timestamp":1778780541384,"sessionID":"ses_1d875521dffeRFwpChqm8uVGYC","part":{"id":"prt_e279501ca001iziPOSGRlmQFsn","messageID":"msg_e2794edcd001Uk42hPLhoj3y1Q","sessionID":"ses_1d875521dffeRFwpChqm8uVGYC","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** The hypothesis proposes a structural optimization to `rtl/alu.sv` that collapses three independent 64-bit multipliers (`mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, `mul_su`) into a single unsigned 64-bit product (`mul_uu`) plus two cheap 32-bit correction subtractors. The math is exact for all RV32M multiply variants (MUL, MULH, MULHU, MULHSU) and was verified with 10,000 random vectors plus edge cases. By removing two redundant multipliers, the design should shed ~1,500–2,000 LUTs/DSPs, relieve routing congestion at the current 99 % LUT utilization, and shorten the M-path combinational delay with zero IPC impact.","time":{"start":1778780537290,"end":1778780541383}}}
