{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778753973520,"sessionID":"ses_1da081598ffelSLGjQATF56q6S","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"grep:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"mdu|multiply|divider|div_unit|mul_unit","path":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores","include":"*.sv"},"output":"Found 16 matches\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/v1/rtl/ex_stage.sv:\n  Line 97:   div_unit u_div (\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/v1/rtl/div_unit.sv:\n  Line 1: // rtl/div_unit.sv\n\n  Line 3: // Iterative RV32M divider/remainder unit. The EX stage starts it only for\n\n  Line 4: // DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU and bubbles EX/MEM until done, keeping the cold divider\n\n  Line 6: module div_unit (\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/v1/rtl/alu.sv:\n  Line 4: // remains here; DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU are handled by div_unit.sv so the FPGA\n\n  Line 5: // divider/remainder hardware is not part of every ALU-result path.\n\n  Line 52:     // M-extension multiply. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS the hardware\n\n  Line 55:     // divide/remainder ALTOPS substitutions live in div_unit.sv.\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/ibex/rtl/ibex_id_stage.sv:\n  Line 810:                 // When single-cycle multiply is configured mul can finish in the first cycle so\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/ibex/rtl/ibex_pkg.sv:\n  Line 195:     // Multiplier/divider\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/ibex/rtl/ibex_ex_block.sv:\n  Line 194:   // Multiplier/divider may require multiple cycles. The ALU output is valid in the same cycle\n\n\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/ibex/rtl/ibex_cs_regist