{"type":"text","timestamp":1778756336588,"sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a84affe3RilYSpocuFUh4","part":{"id":"prt_e2623b25100107Pw4a9rkiK2oi","messageID":"msg_e26238a99001IxaDy6ZLayZZFr","sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a84affe3RilYSpocuFUh4","type":"text","text":"Wrote the structural hypothesis to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r2s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Move branch/jump resolution from EX to ID stage. This cuts the taken control-flow penalty from 2 cycles to 1, which should improve CoreMark IPC (tight loops and function calls dominate). Forwarding paths from EX/MEM and MEM/WB into ID let dependent branches resolve without stalling, while a new load-to-branch stall covers the case where a branch needs a load result that hasn't returned yet. An `early_redirect` flag pipelined to EX prevents double-flushing.","time":{"start":1778756334162,"end":1778756336587}}}
