ere previously hidden in parallel with the ALU's longer delay; moving them upstream creates new critical paths in lighter stages and worsens overall Fmax.\n- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-002-r3s1 (broken, n/a): MEM-to-EX load forwarding to eliminate load-use stalls fails rvfi_reg_check when the forwarded value doesn't exactly match the WB write value; the combinational forward path must replicate the full mem_stage byte-alignment and sign-extension logic, not forward raw dmem_rdata.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/LESSONS.md","time":{"start":1778760941932,"end":1778760941935}},"id":"prt_e266a0033001mTNP18sLhcLdGE","sessionID":"ses_1d9986e2cffeRLNJfRC5OOOvq0","messageID":"msg_e2667920d001aED2cUwow6F9Bk"}}
