0514-002-r4s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Forward exact load result from MEM to EX and remove load-use stall\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls ID for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark's list-walk, matrix-access, and pointer-chasing patterns contain a\\nhigh density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops, so this bubble is a\\nsignificant IPC limiter. Prior attempts either failed to remove the\\naccompanying hazard-unit interlock (producing a no-op) or forwarded raw\\ndmem_rdata without byte-alignment/sign-extension (breaking RVFI reg checks).\\nBy forwarding the fully processed load_data from the MEM-stage combinational\\noutput directly into the existing EX/MEM forward path, and explicitly deleting\\nthe load_use_hazard stall logic, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle with the exact same value that will later be written to the\\nregfile.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The baseline 5-stage pipeline stalls ID for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause the load data is only available after it is latched into MEM/WB.\\nCoreMark's list-walk, matrix-access, and pointer-chasing patterns contain a\\nhigh density of back-to-back load-dependent ALU ops, so this bubble is a\\nsignificant IPC limiter. Prior attempts either failed to remove the\\naccompanying hazard-unit interlock (producing a no-op) or forwarded raw\\ndmem_rdata without byte-alignment/sign-extension (breaking RVFI reg checks).\\nBy forwarding the fully processed load_data from the MEM-stage combinational\\noutput directly into the existing EX/MEM forward path, and explicitly deleting\\nthe load_use_hazard stall logic, the dependent instruction can enter EX on the\\nvery next cycle with the exact same value that will later be written to the\\nregfile.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"1. In mem_stage.sv, expose the internal combinational `load_data` signal as a\\n   new output port `load_data_out`. This is the same byte-aligned,\\n   sign/zero-extended value that is captured into the MEM/WB register.\\n2. In core.sv, change the `fwd_ex_mem` connection fed into ex_stage from a\\n   plain `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to the multiplexed value\\n   `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n   Because the existing forward_unit already asserts select `2'd1` whenever\\n   the EX/MEM instruction writes the matching `rd`, the EX-stage operand mux\\n   will automatically pick up the actual load result instead of the memory\\n   address.\\n3. In hazard_unit.sv, delete the `load_use_hazard` logic entirely. The signal\\n   must be hard-wired to 0 so the pipeline no longer stalls IF/ID on this\\n   case. The remaining stall sources (imem_ready, dmem_ready, redirect) are\\n   untouched.\\n\\nNo new forwarding select encoding is introduced, no EX-stage operand mux\\ngrows beyond its existing 3-way shape, and the forwarded value is bit-exact\\nwith the WB write path, so RVFI reg checks should pass cleanly.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it to the\\ninternal combinational `load_data` signal that is already computed for\\nthe MEM/WB register.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a local wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` connected to\\n`u_mem.load_data_out`. Change the `fwd_ex_mem` port connection on\\n`u_ex` from `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n`ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove all logic that derives `load_use_hazard` from `id_ex_mem_read`,\\n`id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, and `if_id_rs2`. Tie `load_use_hazard` to 0.\\nKeep the port declarations (or remove them and their connections in\\ncore.sv) \\u2014 the minimal change is to keep the ports and simply not use\\nthem inside the combinational block.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add an output port `logic [31:0] load_data_out` and assign it to the\\ninternal combinational `load_data` signal that is already computed for\\nthe MEM/WB register.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a local wire `logic [31:0] mem_load_data` connected to\\n`u_mem.load_data_out`. Change the `fwd_ex_mem` port connection on\\n`u_ex` from `ex_mem_w.alu_result` to\\n`ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read ? mem_load_data : ex_mem_w.alu_result`.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove all logic that derives `load_use_hazard` from `id_ex_mem_read`,\\n`id_ex_rd`, `if_id_rs1`, and `if_id_rs2`. Tie `load_use_hazard` to 0.\\nKeep the port declarations (or remove them and their connections in\\ncore.sv) \\u2014 the minimal change is to keep the ports and simply not use\\nthem inside the combinational block.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"implementation_compile_failed: \",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 4,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-002-r4s1 (broken, n/a): MEM-to-EX load forwarding can reuse the existing forward_unit select encoding by muxing the fwd_ex_mem data source in core.sv; adding unused ports to forward_unit caused an implementation compile failure from unconnected inputs.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Print structural hypothesis outcomes","truncated":false},"title":"Print structural hypothesis outcomes","time":{"start":1778764638966,"end":1778764638968}},"id