{"type":"text","timestamp":1778766762527,"sessionID":"ses_1d93f6632ffefVNacNrTr0HXtD","part":{"id":"prt_e26c2b839001T2lyfmPgY8oSME","messageID":"msg_e26c29edb0014vBLDRZMTnM9XS","sessionID":"ses_1d93f6632ffefVNacNrTr0HXtD","type":"text","text":"Done — the hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r6s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the structural hypothesis:**\n- **Goal:** Eliminate the 1-cycle load-use stall by forwarding the exact, byte-aligned/sign-extended `load_data` from the MEM stage to the EX stage.\n- **Key insight:** `mem_stage` already computes `load_data` combinationally; previous attempts failed because they didn't reuse this exact signal. By exposing it as an output and muxing it into the existing `fwd_ex_mem` path in `core.sv`, the forwarded value will bit-exactly match what eventually gets written back.\n- **Structural changes:** \n  1. `rtl/mem_stage.sv` — add `load_data` output port\n  2. `rtl/core.sv` — select `load_data` when `ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read` is true for the EX→EX forward source\n  3. `rtl/hazard_unit.sv` — remove `load_use_hazard` from stall/flush logic, allowing the dependent instruction to proceed into EX while the LOAD is in MEM\n\nThis reuses the existing `forward_unit` encoding (`fwd_rs1_sel`/`fwd_rs2_sel` = `2'b01`) and requires no changes to `ex_stage` or `forward_unit`.","time":{"start":1778766755897,"end":1778766762526}}}
