{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778769966164,"sessionID":"ses_1d9115b2dffezi8k1kIeeeABPh","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r7s1\ntitle: Merge ID and EX into single 4-stage pipeline\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current 5-stage pipeline pays a 2-cycle penalty for every taken branch and\n  unconditional jump because branch resolution happens in EX, flushing IF and ID.\n  CoreMark has a significant fraction of control-flow instructions; collapsing ID\n  and EX into one combinational stage cuts the mispredict/jump penalty to 1 cycle.\n  In addition, by exposing the MEM stage's extracted load_data as a forward source,\n  load-use hazards can be resolved via forwarding rather than stall, eliminating the\n  1-cycle load-use bubble entirely.\nhypothesis: |\n  Restructure the pipeline from IF-ID-EX-MEM-WB (5 stages) to IF-ID/EX-MEM-WB\n  (4 stages).  A new id_ex_stage module performs decode, regfile read, immediate\n  generation, operand forwarding, ALU execution, and branch resolution all in one\n  combinational cloud, capturing results in a single pipeline register that feeds\n  MEM.  The mem_stage gains a combinational forward_data output (mem_to_reg ?\n  load_data : alu_result) so the forward_unit can source the freshest register\n  value from the MEM stage itself, removing the need for load-use stalls.\n  hazard_unit is simplified: load_use detection is removed, dmem stalls freeze the\n  ID/EX register and bubble IF as before, and redirects kill only the single\n  instruction in flight behind the branch.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 10\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/id_ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      New merged stage replacing id_stage and ex_stage. Combinational decode,\n      regfile read, imm_gen, operand forwarding (from MEM stage and MEM/WB),\n      ALU, branch/jump resolve, and misalign trap. Single registered output\n      (ex_mem_t) feeding MEM stage. JAL/JALR/BNE/etc. resolved here.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Rewire 4-stage topology (IF -> ID/EX -> MEM -> WB). Connect mem_stage\n      forward_data to the EX operand muxes. Remove id_stage and ex_stage\n      instances, instantiate id_ex_stage. Adjust hazard/forward wiring.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Remove load_use_hazard and associated stall/flush logic. In 4-stage with\n      MEM forwarding, load-use is handled by the forward path. Keep imem/dmem\n      stall and redirect flush logic, adapted so redirect only flushes IF and\n      bubbles the single ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add combinational forward_data output that exposes the value that will be\n      written to the register file (load_data for LOADs, alu_result otherwise).\n      This lets the ID/EX stage forward the MEM-stage result combinationally,\n      eliminating load-use stalls.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      No functional change; the existing 2-bit select encoding (01 = stage ahead,\n      10 = stage two ahead) is reused. The data source for the 01 select is now\n      mem_stage.forward_data instead of ex_mem_w.alu_result.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778769966142,"end":1778769966162}},"id":"prt_e26f376e4001DkrxYQJUkIieSr","sessionID":"ses_1d9115b2dffezi8k1kIeeeABPh","messageID":"msg_e26eea515001g7iuHv7s8X98kQ"}}
