eavy and makes frequent function\\ncalls, so backward branches and JALs are a large fraction of dynamic control-flow.\\nA stateless Backward-Taken / Forward-Not-taken (BTFN) predictor costs almost no\\nstate, adds only a small amount of combinational logic in the IF stage, and can\\neliminate the flush penalty on loop back-edges and unconditional jumps.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a BTFN predictor to the IF stage:\\n  - JAL is always predicted taken (target = PC + JAL imm, known in IF).\\n  - Conditional branches are predicted taken only when their immediate is negative\\n    (backward branch), otherwise not-taken.\\n  - JALR is not predicted (falls through) because the target depends on a register\\n    value not visible in IF.\\n  - The predicted target is validated in the same cycle it is produced; if the\\n    computed target is misaligned ([1:0] != 0) the prediction is suppressed and\\n    IF falls back to PC+4, matching the trap-and-fallthrough semantics.\\n\\nChange the EX-stage redirect semantics from \\\"taken branch/jump\\\" to \\\"mispredict\\\":\\n  - EX always computes the architecturally correct next-PC (pc_next / pc_wdata)\\n    from the actual branch/jump resolution, independent of prediction.\\n  - redirect is asserted only when the actual outcome differs from the BTFN\\n    prediction (JALR always mispredicts, backward branches mispredict when not\\n    taken, forward branches mispredict when taken).\\n  - redirect_target is driven from the actual resolved target, not the prediction.\\n  - This preserves RVFI correctness because pc_wdata never depends on the\\n    predictor state.\\n\\nWith this change, correctly predicted JALs and loop-back branches cost 0 flush\\ncycles instead of 2, directly improving CoreMark IPC.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Insert BTFN prediction combinational logic before the PC register. Compute JAL target and BRANCH target from the raw fetched instruction. Drive next_pc from the predicted target for JAL and backward branches, unless the target is misaligned. Pass no extra state through the pipeline bundle; EX recomputes the prediction locally.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace redirect = (branch_taken || is_jump) with mispredict detection: JAL is never a mispredict, JALR is always a mispredict, conditional branches mispredict when branch_taken != imm[31]. Drive redirect_target and pc_next from the actual resolved target (same as architectural next-PC). Ensure misalign_fault still suppresses redirect and forces pc_next = PC+4.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Insert BTFN prediction combinational logic before the PC register. Compute JAL target and BRANCH target from the raw fetched instruction. Drive next_pc from the predicted target for JAL and backward branches, unless the target is misaligned. Pass no extra state through the pipeline bundle; EX recomputes the prediction locally.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace redirect = (branch_taken || is_jump) with mispredict detection: JAL is never a mispredict, JALR is always a mispredict, conditional branches mispredict when branch_taken != imm[31]. Drive redirect_target and pc_next from the actual resolved target (same as architectural next-PC). Ensure misalign_fault still suppresses redirect and forces pc_next = PC+4.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: pc_fwd_ch0\\n pass\\nSBY 11:30:22 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:30:22 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:30:22 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 11:30:22 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: e