{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778778271776,"sessionID":"ses_1d88e88c8ffeinpauws2BWqQqd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /Users/bonetto/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e27724a47001QNqX8DKL9R1AvX | python3 -c \"import sys,json; [print(json.dumps(j)) for line in sys.stdin for j in [json.loads(line)] if j.get('id')=='hyp-20260514-003-r1s2']\"","description":"Get specific predictor entry"},"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"32-entry 2-bit dynamic branch predictor in IF stage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches pc+4 and only redirects after a branch resolves in EX,\\ncosting a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch. CoreMark is loop-heavy; even a\\nsimple dynamic predictor eliminates most of these bubbles, directly improving IPC.\\nA 32-entry PHT adds only 64 flops and a small combinational read port, well within\\nthe ~400 LUT4 headroom on the Tang Nano 20K.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches pc+4 and only redirects after a branch resolves in EX,\\ncosting a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch. CoreMark is loop-heavy; even a\\nsimple dynamic predictor eliminates most of these bubbles, directly improving IPC.\\nA 32-entry PHT adds only 64 flops and a small combinational read port, well within\\nthe ~400 LUT4 headroom on the Tang Nano 20K.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter branch predictor (PHT) indexed by PC[6:2].\\nIn the IF stage, detect conditional branches (opcode 1100011) and JAL (opcode 1101111);\\nextract the immediate via a small imm_gen instance and compute target = pc + imm.\\nQuery the PHT for branches; always predict JAL as taken. A new predict_taken bit is\\nadded to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles. In EX, redirect is asserted only on\\nmispredict (predicted != actual outcome), with the redirect target selecting the\\ncorrect path (branch target or pc+4). The PHT is updated when a branch resolves in EX.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/branch_predictor.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT module with async read and synchronous update.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add branch/JAL detection, imm_gen instance, target adder, and predictor integration to compute next_pc. Output predict_taken in IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Pass predict_taken from IF/ID into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Change redirect logic to compare predicted vs actual outcome. Add predictor update output ports (update_en, update_pc, update_taken).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate branch_predictor, wire update signals from EX stage to predictor, and pass predict_taken through the pipeline.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/branch_predictor.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT module with async read and synchronous update.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add branch/JAL detection, imm_gen instance, target adder, and predictor integration to compute next_pc. Output predict_taken in IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Pass predict_taken from IF/ID into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Change redirect logic to compare predicted vs actual outcome. Add predictor update output ports (update_en, update_pc, update_taken).\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"descripti