{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778778302791,"sessionID":"ses_1d88e88c8ffeinpauws2BWqQqd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sed -n '23p' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -m json.tool | head -n 40","description":"Read line 23 of log"},"output":"{\n    \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\",\n    \"title\": \"Split ALU into fast and M-extension paths with final 2:1 mux\",\n    \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n    \"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": {\n        \"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n        \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure rtl/alu.sv so that:\\n1. A \\\"fast\\\" always_comb block computes ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SLT,\\n   SLTU, SLL, SRL, SRA, and LUI into a local `fast_out` variable.\\n2. A separate \\\"muldiv\\\" always_comb block (guarded by the existing\\n   opcode if-gate) computes the 64-bit products and DIV/REM results\\n   into a local `m_out` variable.\\n3. A final assignment `out = (op >= ALU_MUL) ? m_out : fast_out;`\\n   drives the output through a single 2:1 mux instead of a 19:1 case\\n   statement.  This keeps the ALTOPS branch intact and does not change\\n   any bit-level results.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n        {\n            \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n            \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n    \"fitness\": 396.13,\n    \"delta_pct\": 18.48,\n    \"vs_baseline\": 40.06,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 165.51,\n    \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n    \"cycles\": 4178194,\n    \"iterations\": 10,\n    \"lut4\": 9927,\n    \"ff\": 1874,\n    \"seeds\": [\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n    \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\",\n    \"title\": \"Split ALU into fast and M-extension paths with final 2:1 mux\",\n    \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n    \"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": {\n        \"motivation\": \"A prior hypothesis proved that gating multiply evaluation inside alu.sv\\nraises Fmax by removing multiplier hardware from the critical path of\\nnon-M ops.  However, the ALU still selects its result through a single\\n19-entry case statement where the large multiplier/divider outputs are\\ninputs to the same mux tree as the fast ADD/SUB/LOGIC/SHIFT ops.\\nSynthesis tools may not fully prune those heavy inputs from the fast-path\\nmux delay.  By explicitly separating the ALU into a fast path (ADD/SUB/\\nLOGIC/SHIFT/SLT/LUI) and a slow M-extension path (MUL/DIV/REM) and\\nselecting between them with a single 2:1 mux, the fast path sees a much\\nsmaller combinational cloud and should achieve a slightly higher Fmax\\nwith zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n        \"hypothesis\": \"Restructure rtl/alu.sv so that:\\n1. A \\\"fast\\\" always_comb block computes ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR, SLT,\\n   SLTU, SLL, SRL, SRA, and LUI into a local `fast_out` variable.\\n2. A separate \\\"muldiv\\\" always_comb block (guarded by the existing\\n   opcode if-gate) computes the 64-bit products and DIV/REM results\\n   into a local `m_out` variable.\\n3. A final assignment `out = (op >= ALU_MUL) ? m_out : fast_out;`\\n   drives the output through a single 2:1 mux instead of a 19:1 case\\n   statement.  This keeps the ALTOPS branch intact and does not change\\n   any bit-level results.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n        {\n            \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n            \"description\": \"Split the single always_comb block into a fast path for base-integer\\nops, a guarded M-extension path, and a final 2:1 mux.  The fast path\\nuses a smaller case statement (11 entries) and the M path keeps the\\nexisting guarded multiply/divide logic.  No other files are touched.\\n\"\n        }\n    ],\n    \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n    \"fitness\": 396.13,\n    \"delta_pct\": 18.48,\n    \"vs_baseline\": 40.06,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 165.51,\n    \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n    \"cycles\": 4178194,\n    \"iterations\": 10,\n    \"lut4\": 9927,\n    \"ff\": 1874,\n    \"seeds\": [\n","exit":0,"description":"Read line 23 of log","truncated":false},"title":"Read line 23 of log","time":{"start":1778778302785,"end":1778778302790}},"id":"prt_e2772e75e001NmNVmm2r9BX182","sessionID":"ses_1d