{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778778309815,"sessionID":"ses_1d88e88c8ffeinpauws2BWqQqd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sed -n '15p' cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -m json.tool | head -n 30","description":"Read line 15 of log"},"output":"{\n    \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\",\n    \"title\": \"8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in IF to absorb imem stalls\",\n    \"category\": \"structural\",\n    \"motivation\": \"The fitness metric multiplies FPGA Fmax (measured with zero-wait imem) by\\nCoreMark IPC (measured under ~22% random imem stalls). The baseline stalls\\nthe entire front-end on every imem backpressure cycle, inserting a bubble.\\nAn 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in the IF stage can serve cached\\ninstructions during stalls, improving IPC. Because the FPGA bench ties\\nio_imemReady to 1'b1, the cache-read path is dead in synthesis and will be\\npruned by Yosys, leaving Fmax and area unchanged.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": {\n        \"motivation\": \"The fitness metric multiplies FPGA Fmax (measured with zero-wait imem) by\\nCoreMark IPC (measured under ~22% random imem stalls). The baseline stalls\\nthe entire front-end on every imem backpressure cycle, inserting a bubble.\\nAn 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in the IF stage can serve cached\\ninstructions during stalls, improving IPC. Because the FPGA bench ties\\nio_imemReady to 1'b1, the cache-read path is dead in synthesis and will be\\npruned by Yosys, leaving Fmax and area unchanged.\\n\",\n        \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache inside if_stage. The cache\\nis indexed by pc[4:2] with a 27-bit tag (pc[31:5]). On each cycle where\\nimem_ready is high and there is no redirect, the fetched instruction updates\\nthe indexed entry. A new combinational icache_hit output is driven when\\nthe current PC matches a valid tag. hazard_unit receives icache_hit and\\nsuppresses imem_stall when the cache hits: imem_stall = !imem_ready &&\\n!icache_hit. Consequently stall_if and flush_if are not asserted on a\\ncache hit, allowing the PC to advance and the pipeline to consume the\\ncached instruction even while the bus is stalled. The cache data path is\\nexplicitly gated by !imem_ready so formal and FPGA zero-wait modes always\\nuse the live imem_data and never see stale cached values.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Add 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache arrays (data, tag, valid)\\nindexed by pc[4:2]. Add output port icache_hit and input port\\nimem_ready. Update cache on imem_ready && !redirect. Modify the\\ncombinational output so that when !imem_ready && icache_hit the\\nstage emits the cached instruction and keeps valid high; otherwise\\nretain baseline behavior (NOP on flush, imem_data when ready).\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Add input icache_hit. Change imem_stall from !imem_ready to\\n(!imem_ready && !icache_hit). Leave stall_id, flush_id, and all\\nother stall/flush logic untouched so load-use and dmem stalls still\\nfreeze the PC.\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Wire io_imemReady into if_stage as imem_ready. Wire the new\\nicache_hit output from if_stage into hazard_unit. No top-level IO\\nchanges.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n    \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\",\n    \"title\": \"8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in IF to absorb imem stalls\",\n    \"category\": \"structural\",\n    \"motivation\": \"The fitness metric multiplies FPGA Fmax (measured with zero-wait imem) by\\nCoreMark IPC (measured under ~22% random imem stalls). The baseline stalls\\nthe entire front-end on every imem backpressure cycle, inserting a bubble.\\nAn 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in the IF stage can serve cached\\ninstructions during stalls, improving IPC. Because the FPGA bench ties\\nio_imemReady to 1'b1, the cache-read path is dead in synthesis and will be\\npruned by Yosys, leaving Fmax and area unchanged.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": {\n        \"motivation\": \"The fitness metric multiplies FPGA Fmax (measured with zero-wait imem) by\\nCoreMark IPC (measured under ~22% random imem stalls). The baseline stalls\\nthe entire front-end on every imem backpressure cycle, inserting a bubble.\\nAn 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache in the IF stage can serve cached\\ninstructions during stalls, improving IPC. Because the FPGA bench ties\\nio_imemReady to 1'b1, the cache-read path is dead in synthesis and will be\\npruned by Yosys, leaving Fmax and area unchanged.\\n\",\n        \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache inside if_stage. The cache\\nis indexed by pc[4:2] with a 27-bit tag (pc[31:5]). On each cycle where\\nimem_ready is high and there is no redirect, the fetched instruction updates\\nthe indexed entry. A new combinational icache_hit output is driven when\\nthe current PC matches a valid tag. hazard_unit receives icache_hit and\\nsuppresses imem_stall when the cache hits: imem_stall = !imem_ready &&\\n!icache_hit. Consequently stall_if and flush_if are not asserted on a\\ncache hit, allowing the PC to advance and the pipeline to consume the\\ncached instruction even while the bus is stalled. The cache data path is\\nexplicitly gated by !imem_ready so formal and FPGA zero-wait modes always\\nuse the live imem_data and never see stale cached values.\\n\",\n        \"expected_impact\": {\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n            \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n        },\n        \"changes\": [\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Add 8-entry direct-mapped instruction cache arrays (data, tag, valid)\\nindexed by pc[4:2]. Add output port icache_hit and input port\\nimem_ready. Update cache on imem_ready && !redirect. Modify the\\ncombinational output so that when !imem_ready && icache_hit the\\nstage emits the cached instruction and keeps valid high; otherwise\\nretain baseline behavior (NOP on flush, imem_data when ready).\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Add input icache_hit. Change imem_stall from !imem_ready to\\n(!imem_ready && !icache_hit). Leave stall_id, flush_id, and all\\nother stall/flush logic untouched so load-use and dmem stalls still\\nfreeze the PC.\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n                \"description\": \"Wire io_imemReady into if_stage as imem_ready. Wire the new\\nicache_hit output from if_stage into hazard_unit. No top-level IO\\nchanges.\\n\"\n            }\n        ]\n    },\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 6,\n        \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n","exit":0,"description":"Read line 15 of log","truncated":false},"title":"Read line 15 of log","time":{"start":1778778309806,"end":1778778309814}},"id":"prt_e277302ba001NMndZRJIPjs4hj","sessionID":"ses_1d88e88c8ffeinpauws2BWqQqd","messageID":"msg_e2772ea2e001wUcabmuPswjbP2"}}
