 = icache_data[cache_idx][31]`\n22:       `predict_taken = icache_hit && pred_valid[cache_idx] &&\n23:                        (pred_tag[cache_idx] == cache_tag) &&\n24:                        !flush && !redirect &&\n25:                        (is_jal || (is_branch && is_backward))`\n26:       `next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target :\n27:                  predict_taken ? pred_target[cache_idx] : pc + 32'd4;`\n28:   - In ex_stage, change redirect to mispredict-only and expose update outputs:\n29:       `actual_taken    = in.ctrl.is_jump || branch_taken;`\n30:       `redirect        = ((!in.predict_taken && actual_taken) ||\n31:                           (in.predict_taken && (!actual_taken || misalign_fault)))\n32:                          && !misalign_fault;`\n33:       `redirect_target = misalign_fault          ? (in.pc + 32'd4) :\n34:                          !actual_taken           ? (in.pc + 32'd4) :\n35:                          in.ctrl.is_jump         ? jump_target :\n36:                                                    branch_target;`\n37:       `pred_update       = !misalign_fault && in.valid &&\n38:                            ((in.ctrl.is_jump && !in.ctrl.is_jalr) ||\n39:                             (in.ctrl.is_branch && branch_taken && in.imm[31]));`\n40:       `pred_update_idx   = in.pc[4:2];`\n41:       `pred_update_tag   = in.pc[31:5];`\n42:       `pred_update_target = redirect_target;`\n43:   - Leave the EX/MEM `pc_next` register assignment completely untouched so\n44:     rvfi_pc_fwd stays correct.\n45:   - In core.sv, wire the four `pred_update*` outputs from u_ex into new inputs\n46:     on u_if, and pass `predict_taken` through the existing struct bundles.\n47:   - Reset clears all `pred_valid`; EX updates set `pred_valid`+`pred_tag`+`pred_target`\n48:     synchronously.  No eviction-clear logic is required because the tag match\n49:     suppresses stale entries automatically.\n50: expected_impact:\n51:   fitness_delta_pct: 5\n52:   confidence: medium\n53: changes:\n54:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n55:     description: |\n56:       Add a single `logic predict_taken;` field to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t`\n57:       pipeline bundles so the prediction flag travels with the instruction.\n58:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n59:     description: |\n60:       1. Add `pred_valid[0:7]`, `pred_tag[0:7][26:0]`, `pred_target[0:7][31:0]` arrays.\n61:       2. On reset clear all `pred_valid`.\n62:       3. Accept new inputs `pred_update`, `pred_update_idx[2:0]`,\n63:          `pred_update_tag[26:0]`, `pred_update_target[31:0]`.\n64:       4. On `pred_update` write `pred_valid[pred_update_idx] <= 1'b1`,\n65:          `pred_tag[pred_update_idx] <= pred_update_tag`,\n66:          `pred_target[pred_update_idx] <= pred_update_target`.\n67:       5. Combinational prediction uses the cached instruction opcode/sign bit\n68:          gated by `icache_hit`, `pred_valid`, and tag equality.\n69:       6. `next_pc` becomes a 3:1 mux: redirect_target, pred_target, or pc+4.\n70:       7. Drive `out.predict_taken` with the combinational prediction signal.\n71:       8. Keep all existing I-cache logic unchanged.\n72:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n73:     description: |\n74:       Capture `in.predict_taken` into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.\n75:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n76:     description: |\n77:       1. Read `in.predict_taken`.\n78:       2. Replace unconditional redirect with mispredict-only redirect using\n79:          `actual_taken` and `misalign_fault` exactly as specified.\n80:       3. Drive `redirect_target` so a predicted-taken / not-taken mispredict\n81:          recovers to pc+4.\n82:       4. Leave the EX/MEM `pc_next` register assignment completely untouched.\n83:       5. Add combinational `pred_update*` outputs that fire for JAL or taken\n84:          backward branches, gated by `!misalign_fault && in.valid`.\n85:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n86:     description: |\n87:       Wire the four `pred_update*` outputs from `u_ex` to the new inputs on\n88:       `u_if`.  Pass `predict_taken` through the existing `if_id_t` connection\n89:       to `u_id`.  No other top-level changes.\n\n(End of file - total 89 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\ntitle: ICache-integrated JAL/backward-branch predictor with tag-matched retention\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline with an 8-entry I-cache and ALU fast path achieves 396.13 fitness,\n  but still flushes IF/ID on every taken JAL and backward branch, costing two cycles.\n  A prior attempt to integrate target prediction into the I-cache (hyp-20260514-003-r9s2)\n  produced exactly 0 % delta because the predictor valid bit was cleared on every\n  cache refill, so predictions were never visible when the branch PC was fetched again.\n  By storing a partial tag with each prediction entry and qualifying the hit with\n  tag equality, the predictor state survives across repeated fetches and evictions\n  without needing explicit invalidation logic.  This reuses the existing fast I-cache\n  read path (registered state, no external imem_data combinational delay) and adds\n  only ~250 FFs and a small next-pc mux, well within the remaining LUT4 headroom.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend the existing 8-entry I-cache in if_stage.sv with a tiny target predictor:\n  - Add `pred_valid[0:7]`, `pred_tag[0:7][26:0]`, and `pred_target[0:7][31:0]`.\n  - Combinational prediction (no imem_data in the path):\n      `is_jal      = (icache_data[cache_idx][6:0] == 7'b1101111)`\n      `is_branch   = (icache_data[cache_idx][6:0] == 7'b1100011)`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r10s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778778573063,"end":1778778573076}},"id":"prt_e2777057b0014nvJyTz7xy00u1","sessionID":"ses_1d88e88c8ffeinpauws2BWqQqd","messageID":"msg_e2776f385001LnZAR0mvkbHMpl"}}
