\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:57  Writing trace to Verilog testbench: engine_0/trace_tb.v\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:57  Writing trace to constraints file: engine_0/trace.smtc\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:57  Writing trace to Yosys witness file: engine_0/trace.yw\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:57  Status: failed\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=1)\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: FAIL\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:58 (58)\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:42 (42)\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned FAIL\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: counterexample trace: insn_beq_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] summary:   failed assertion rvfi_testbench._witness_.check_flatten_checker_inst__assert_rvfi_insn_check_sv_198_154 at rvfi_insn_check.sv:198.6-198.31 step 20\\nSBY 10:42:56 [insn_beq_ch0] DONE (FAIL, rc=0)\\n\\nFull run log: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2/formal/last_run-49124.log\\nPer-check logs in: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2/formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench-49124/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 5, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-003-r5s2 (broken, n/a): A unified `predict_taken` bit used for both branches and jumps cannot be compared against `branch_taken` in the redirect condition because jumps are always taken yet `branch_taken` is zero for JAL; this causes a false mispredict redirect on every correctly predicted jump, corrupting the RVFI trace.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r6s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv']\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 6, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage recomputes pc+4 in two places (JAL return address and fall-through\\npc_next) and uses a full 32-bit pc+imm adder for misalignment checks that feed\\nthe redirect signal back to IF. On FPGA this adds combinational delay to the\\ncritical path. Since IF already computes pc+4 for next_pc, and RV32I guarantees\\npc[1:0]=0 and branch/jump immediate[0]=0, we can eliminate adders from the\\nredirect/misalign path without changing semantics.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"1. Pre-compute pc+4 in if_stage and pass it through if_id_t and id_ex_t so\\n   ex_stage uses the pipelined value instead of recomputing pc+4.\\n2. Simplify branch and JAL misalignment checks to use in.imm[1] instead of\\n   (pc+imm)[1:0], removing the pc+imm adder from the misalign_fault path.\\n3. Collapse the EX/MEM pc_next mux to `redirect ? redirect_target : pc_plus_4`,\\n   which is equivalent because `redirect` already incorporates `!misalign_fault`.\\n4. Remove the unused `branch_target` field from ex_mem_t to save 32 FFs and\\n   reduce routing.\\nThese changes shorten the EX->IF redirect critical path and reduce EX\\ncombinational logic, raising Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `pc_plus_4` to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t`. Remove unused `branch_target` from `ex_mem_t`.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Drive `out.pc_plus_4 = pc + 32'd4` in the combinational IF/ID bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Capture `in.pc_plus_4` into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use `in.pc_plus_4` for JAL return address and pc_next fall-through. Simplify misalign checks: branches/JAL use `in.imm[1]`; JALR uses `jalr_sum[1]`. Collapse pc_next to `redirect ? redirect_target : in.pc_plus_4`. Remove `branch_target` assignment.\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r6s1\", \"title\": \"Forward exact load_data from MEM to EX to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The 5-stage pipeline currently stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard.\\nCoreMark contains frequent pointer-chasing and array indexing patterns that\\ntrigger these stalls. Previous attempts failed because the forwarded value\\ndid not exactly match the WB write value. mem_stage already computes the\\nfully byte-aligned and sign-extended load_data combinationally; exposing it\\nto the EX-stage forward mux allows us to remove the stall entirely without\\nduplicating extraction logic.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The 5-stage pipeline currently stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard.\\nCoreMark contains frequent pointer-chasing and array indexing patterns that\\ntrigger these stalls. Previous attempts failed because the forwarded value\\ndid not exactly match the WB write value. mem_stage already computes the\\nfully byte-aligned and sign-extended load_data combinationally; exposing it\\nto the EX-stage forward mux allows us to remove the stall entirely without\\nduplicating extraction logic.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational load_data output to mem_stage and use it in core.sv to\\ndrive the fwd_ex_mem input to ex_stage whenever the instruction in EX/MEM\\nis a LOAD (ctrl.mem_read). Remove the load_use_hazard detection from\\nhazard_unit so that a dependent instruction can enter EX in the same cycle\\nthe LOAD is in MEM. This reuses the existing forward_unit encoding\\n(fwd_rs1_sel/fwd_rs2_sel = 2'b01) and requires no changes to ex_stage or\\nforward_unit.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the internal combinational load_data signal as an additional output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Mux fwd_ex_mem between ex_mem_w.alu_result and mem_stage.load_data based on ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id logic.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the internal combinational load_data signal as an additional output port.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Mux fwd_ex_mem between ex_mem_w.alu_result and mem_stage.load_data based on ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove load_use_hazard from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id logic.\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\n engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sra_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Status: passed\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY 11:14:22 [insn_sw_ch