{"type":"text","timestamp":1778780570554,"sessionID":"ses_1d875531fffeGkoitkHgyLbHLr","part":{"id":"prt_e27957658002VAfnxgLe4KNNUq","messageID":"msg_e27955378001QSTlWgzPxNMI0j","sessionID":"ses_1d875531fffeGkoitkHgyLbHLr","type":"text","text":"I’ve written the predictor hypothesis to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r11s2.yaml`\n\nThe proposal adds a **16-entry standalone tagged target predictor** that stores its own `predict_taken` bit, avoiding the three failure modes that killed every prior predictor attempt:\n\n1. **No external `imem_data` decode in IF** → safe for Fmax.  \n2. **No dependency on `icache_hit`** → works even when the branch instruction has been evicted from the 8-entry I-cache.  \n3. **Mispredict-only redirect in EX with untouched `pc_next`** → preserves `rvfi_pc_fwd`.\n\nDoubling capacity to 16 entries (vs. the thrashed 8-entry BTB) should capture enough of CoreMark’s hot backward branches and JALs to yield a modest IPC gain without hurting the ALU-fast-path Fmax.","time":{"start":1778780567128,"end":1778780570553}}}
