{"type":"text","timestamp":1778753695353,"sessionID":"ses_1da0815ffffeBXuejAGW6vwgt6","part":{"id":"prt_e25fb53e8001eRhezkiBQazT1v","messageID":"msg_e25fb37c7001yuIxMooD8XUU7K","sessionID":"ses_1da0815ffffeBXuejAGW6vwgt6","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r1s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of the proposed predictor hypothesis:**\n\n- **Approach:** Add a lightweight 32-entry, 2-bit saturating counter branch predictor (PHT) indexed by `PC[6:2]`.\n- **IF-stage integration:** Combinational detection of conditional branches and JAL, immediate extraction via a dedicated `imm_gen` instance, and a target adder to allow fetching the predicted target immediately instead of always `pc+4`.\n- **Pipeline changes:** A single `predict_taken` bit is threaded through the `IF/ID` and `ID/EX` pipeline registers.\n- **EX-stage mispredict recovery:** `redirect` is asserted only when the predicted direction differs from the actual outcome (branch taken/not taken, or aliased non-branch). The redirect target automatically selects either the branch/jump target or the fall-through `pc+4`.\n- **Predictor update:** The PHT is updated when branches resolve in the EX stage.\n- **Resource impact:** ~64 flops + small combinational logic, well within the remaining Tang Nano 20K budget (~400 LUT4). Expected fitness delta: **+10%** (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778753688552,"end":1778753695351}}}
