{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778756313946,"sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a778ffeEgB7IWjbFuvIaA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r2s2\ntitle: Static backward-taken predictor with early JAL resolution in IF\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\n  incurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\n  CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\n  dominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\n  JAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\n  table, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\n  Because the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\n  imem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately—eliminating the\n  redirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add combinational branch/jump prediction to the IF stage and suppress\n  EX-stage redirects when the prediction is correct.\n\n  1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\n  2. In if_stage, instantiate a small imm_gen (or inline equivalent) to\n     extract the B/J immediate from imem_data. Detect opcode 1100011\n     (BRANCH) and 1101111 (JAL). Predict taken for JAL unconditionally,\n     and for branches when the immediate sign bit is 1 (backward branch).\n     On a predicted-taken instruction, redirect next_pc to pc+imm instead\n     of pc+4. This means the sequential fall-through instruction is never\n     fetched, so no flush is needed on a correct prediction.\n  3. In id_stage, pass predict_taken through the ID/EX register.\n  4. In ex_stage, change the redirect condition so it only fires on a\n     mispredict: for branches when branch_taken != predict_taken, and for\n     jumps when predict_taken == 0 (i.e. JALR, which is never predicted).\n     Correctly predicted JALs and backward branches therefore flow through\n     the pipeline with zero bubble penalty.\n\n  This is a much simpler and lower-risk version of the broken 32-entry\n  dynamic-PHT attempt: no stateful structures, no PHT update logic, and a\n  tiny combinational path (opcode compare → imm mux → adder) that reuses\n  the existing pc+4 adder delay budget.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types.\n      Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive\n      next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set\n      out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with\n      mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs\n      from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR).\n      Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r2s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r2s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r2s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778756313943,"end":1778756313946}},"id":"prt_e26232c0a001KnNJfPS7ooxAWX","sessionID":"ses_1d9e1a778ffeEgB7IWjbFuvIaA","messageID":"msg_e26231259001XVT6cr1A5ZZD2u"}}
