t-taken paths). These adders sit between\\nthe ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\\nfrom branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\\nthese values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\\npipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\\ncloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\\nFmax seeds without any IPC change.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The EX stage currently computes two 32-bit additions on its critical path:\\nbranch_target = pc + imm (for branches and JAL) and pc + 4 (for JAL/JALR\\nreturn address and pc_next on not-taken paths). These adders sit between\\nthe ID/EX register and the redirect/pc_next muxes, lengthening the path\\nfrom branch resolution back to the IF stage PC register. By pre-computing\\nthese values in IF (pc+4) and ID (pc+imm) and carrying them through the\\npipeline registers, we remove two 32-bit adders from the EX combinational\\ncloud. This shortens the redirect critical path and should raise worst-case\\nFmax seeds without any IPC change.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t, and add branch_target to id_ex_t.\\nIn if_stage, compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 4. In id_stage, compute\\nbranch_target = in.pc + imm and capture both pc_plus4 and branch_target\\ninto the ID/EX register. In ex_stage, replace every occurrence of\\nin.pc + 4 with in.pc_plus4 and every occurrence of in.pc + in.imm with\\nin.branch_target. This removes the pc+4 and pc+imm adders from EX,\\nleaving only the JALR rs1+imm adder and the ALU itself.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pc_plus4 to if_id_t and id_ex_t; add branch_target to id_ex_t.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute out.pc_plus4 = pc + 32'd4 in the combinational output block.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute branch_target = in.pc + imm combinationally and latch both in.pc_plus4 and branch_target into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace in.pc + 32'd4 with in.pc_plus4 and in.pc + in.imm with in.branch_target. Remove the local branch_target adder and the pc+4 adder.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 289.97, \"delta_pct\": -8.01, \"vs_baseline\": 2.53, \"fmax_mhz\": 130.24, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9475, \"ff\": 1933, \"seeds\": [127.37, 133.0, 130.24], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:09:45.983278Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-001-r2s0 (regression, -8.01%): Pre-computing pc+4 in IF and pc+imm in ID to remove adders from EX backfires because the adders were previously hidden in parallel with the ALU's longer delay; moving them upstream creates new critical paths in lighter stages and worsens overall Fmax.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r2s1\", \"title\": \"Early branch and jump resolution in ID stage\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX,\\ncausing a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark's\\ntight loops and frequent function calls spend a significant fraction of\\ncycles recovering from these mispredicts. Moving branch condition\\nevaluation and jump target computation to the ID stage cuts the penalty\\nto 1 cycle, directly improving iterations/cycle.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX,\\ncausing a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and jump. CoreMark's\\ntight loops and frequent function calls spend a significant fraction of\\ncycles recovering from these mispredicts. Moving branch condition\\nevaluation and jump target computation to the ID stage cuts the penalty\\nto 1 cycle, directly improving iterations/cycle.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Relocate unconditional jump (JAL/JALR) target calculation and conditional\\nbranch resolution from EX to ID. Add operand forwarding paths from\\nEX/MEM and MEM/WB into the ID stage so branches dependent on recent\\nresults resolve without stalling. Introduce a load-to-branch stall in\\nthe hazard unit when a branch in ID consumes a load result still in EX.\\nPipeline an early-redirect flag so EX does not re-assert flush on an\\ninstruction already redirected in ID.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add early_redirect bit to id_ex_t pipeline bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Insert branch target adder, branch condition comparator, and\\nforwarding muxes for rs1/rs2. Drive id_redirect and\\nid_redirect_target to IF stage.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept id_redirect/id_redirect_target and prioritize them over EX redirect.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Assert flush_if (but not flush_id) on id_redirect. Add\\nload-to-branch stall detection when a branch source matches a\\nload in EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Suppress redirect output when the id_ex_t early_redirect flag is set.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire id_redirect signals between stages and update forwarding connections.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add early_redirect bit to id_ex_t pipeline bundle.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Insert branch target adder, branch condition comparator, and\\nforwarding muxes for rs1/rs2. Drive id_redirect and\\nid_redirect_target to IF stage.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept id_redirect/id_redirect_target and prioritize them over EX redirect.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Assert flush_if (but not flush_id) on id_redirect. Add\\nload-to-branch stall detection when a branch source matches a\\nload in EX.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Suppress redirect output when the id_ex_t early_redirect flag is set.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire id_redirect signals between stages and update forwarding connections.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 315.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 11.46, \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10217, \"ff\": 1864, \"seeds\": [146.07, 134.99, 141.58], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:12:30.258336Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 2}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r2s2\", \"title\": \"Static backward-taken predictor with early JAL resolution in IF\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\\nincurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately\\u2014eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\\nincurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately\\u2014eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational branch/jump prediction to the IF stage and suppress\\nEX-stage redirects when the prediction is correct.\\n\\n1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\\n2. In if_stage, instantiate a small imm_gen (or inline equivalent) to\\n   extract the B/J immediate from imem_data. Detect opcode 1100011\\n   (BRANCH) and 1101111 (JAL). Predict taken for JAL unconditionally,\\n   and for branches when the immediate sign bit is 1 (backward branch).\\n   On a predicted-taken instruction, redirect next_pc to pc+imm instead\\n   of pc+4. This means the sequential fall-through instruction is never\\n   fetched, so no flush is needed on a correct prediction.\\n3. In id_stage, pass predict_taken through the ID/EX register.\\n4. In ex_stage, change the redirect condition so it only fires on a\\n   mispredict: for branches when branch_taken != predict_taken, and for\\n   jumps when predict_taken == 0 (i.e. JALR, which is never predicted).\\n   Correctly predicted JALs and backward branches therefore flow through\\n   the pipeline with zero bubble penalty.\\n\\nThis is a much simpler and lower-risk version of the broken 32-entry\\ndynamic-PHT attempt: no stateful structures, no PHT update logic, and a\\ntiny combinational path (opcode compare \\u2192 imm mux \\u2192 adder) that reuses\\nthe existing pc+4 adder delay budget.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 203.63, \"delta_pct\": -35.4, \"vs_baseline\": -28.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 86.74, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10047, \"ff\": 1868, \"seeds\": [86.74, 87.03, 82.66], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:19:46.077886Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 2, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Read recent experiment log entries","truncated":false},"title":"Read recent experiment log entries","time":{"start":1778757954745,"end":1778757954747}},"id":"prt_e263c67f3001n1LHNKYJUJM6LR","sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c403ffe4Rle1T60QoHOUK","messageID":"msg_e263c3c65001O5gFyvdOhayaJx"}}
