{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778758232982,"sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c403ffe4Rle1T60QoHOUK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r3s2\ntitle: 32-entry direct-mapped BTB in IF stage to eliminate taken-branch bubbles\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline always fetches sequentially, paying a 2-cycle bubble for every\n  taken branch and JAL. A prior static predictor that computed branch targets\n  combinationally in IF from imem_data (decode -> imm_gen -> adder) slashed\n  Fmax by ~40% because that path starts from the off-chip/BRAM instruction\n  word. A Branch Target Buffer (BTB) avoids that path entirely: it is indexed\n  directly by the PC register output, so the predicted next PC is just a small\n  distributed-RAM read with no instruction decode or adder in the critical\n  path. On the Tang Nano 20K a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\n  a single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\n  the branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 32-entry direct-mapped BTB to the IF stage.\n  - Read: combinational, indexed by pc[6:2], outputs hit and target[31:0].\n  - Write: registered in EX when a conditional branch or JAL is resolved\n    taken, storing pc[6:2] -> target.\n  - IF stage: next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target : btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4.\n  - Pipeline a predict_taken bit (= btb_hit) through IF/ID and ID/EX.\n  - EX stage: mispredict = (predict_taken != actual_taken). Redirect only on\n    mispredict; correct BTB hits flow through with zero bubble. JALR is never\n    predicted (target depends on rs1).\n  CoreMark's inner loops quickly warm the BTB, after which every loop-back\n  branch costs zero bubbles instead of two. The BTB read path is shorter than\n  the previous static predictor's imem_data->decode->adder path, so Fmax\n  impact should be minimal.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\n  - file: rtl/btb.sv\n    description: New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational\n      read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution\n      from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target\n      on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches\n      EX stage.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert\n      redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en,\n      update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF\n      stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken\n      through the pipeline bundles.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r3s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r3s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r3s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778758232967,"end":1778758232982}},"id":"prt_e26405970001PncCAtvpGehLiB","sessionID":"ses_1d9c3c403ffe4Rle1T60QoHOUK","messageID":"msg_e264021160019DqgnTZrEa3oTD"}}
