{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778760850659,"sessionID":"ses_1d9986e98ffeo1wc7H48Yz9fNk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        obj = json.loads(line)\n        if obj.get('category') == 'predictor':\n            print('---')\n            for k in sorted(obj.keys()):\n                v = obj[k]\n                if isinstance(v, str):\n                    print(f'{k}: len={len(v)}')\n                else:\n                    print(f'{k}: {v}')\n\"","description":"Inspect predictor JSON keys"},"output":"---\ncategory: len=9\nchanges: [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/branch_predictor.sv', 'description': 'New 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT module with async read and synchronous update.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Add branch/JAL detection, imm_gen instance, target adder, and predictor integration to compute next_pc. Output predict_taken in IF/ID bundle.'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Pass predict_taken from IF/ID into the ID/EX register.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Change redirect logic to compare predicted vs actual outcome. Add predictor update output ports (update_en, update_pc, update_taken).'}, {'file': 'rtl/core.sv', 'description': 'Instantiate branch_predictor, wire update signals from EX stage to predictor, and pass predict_taken through the pipeline.'}]\ncosim_passed: False\nerror: len=4027\nexpected_impact: {'fitness_delta_pct': 10, 'confidence': 'medium'}\nformal_passed: False\nhypothesis: {'motivation': 'The baseline always fetches pc+4 and only redirects after a branch resolves in EX,\\ncosting a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch. CoreMark is loop-heavy; even a\\nsimple dynamic predictor eliminates most of these bubbles, directly improving IPC.\\nA 32-entry PHT adds only 64 flops and a small combinational read port, well within\\nthe ~400 LUT4 headroom on the Tang Nano 20K.\\n', 'hypothesis': 'Add a 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter branch predictor (PHT) indexed by PC[6:2].\\nIn the IF stage, detect conditional branches (opcode 1100011) and JAL (opcode 1101111);\\nextract the immediate via a small imm_gen instance and compute target = pc + imm.\\nQuery the PHT for branches; always predict JAL as taken. A new predict_taken bit is\\nadded to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles. In EX, redirect is asserted only on\\nmispredict (predicted != actual outcome), with the redirect target selecting the\\ncorrect path (branch target or pc+4). The PHT is updated when a branch resolves in EX.\\n', 'expected_impact': {'fitness_delta_pct': 10, 'confidence': 'medium'}, 'changes': [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/branch_predictor.sv', 'description': 'New 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT module with async read and synchronous update.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Add branch/JAL detection, imm_gen instance, target adder, and predictor integration to compute next_pc. Output predict_taken in IF/ID bundle.'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Pass predict_taken from IF/ID into the ID/EX register.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Change redirect logic to compare predicted vs actual outcome. Add predictor update output ports (update_en, update_pc, update_taken).'}, {'file': 'rtl/core.sv', 'description': 'Instantiate branch_predictor, wire update signals from EX stage to predictor, and pass predict_taken through the pipeline.'}]}\nid: len=21\nmotivation: len=374\noutcome: len=6\nround_id: 1\nscribe_skipped: len=41\nslot: 2\ntitle: len=51\n---\ncategory: len=9\nchanges: [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n'}]\ncosim_passed: True\ncycles: 4259699\ndelta_pct: -35.4\nerror: None\nexpected_impact: {'fitness_delta_pct': 8, 'confidence': 'medium'}\nff: 1868\nfitness: 203.63\nfmax_mhz: 86.74\nformal_passed: True\nhypothesis: {'motivation': 'The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\\nincurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately—eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n', 'hypothesis': 'Add combinational branch/jump prediction to the IF stage and suppress\\nEX-stage redirects when the prediction is correct.\\n\\n1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\\n2. In if_stage, instantiate a small imm_gen (or inline equivalent) to\\n   extract the B/J immediate from imem_data. Detect opcode 1100011\\n   (BRANCH) and 1101111 (JAL). Predict taken for JAL unconditionally,\\n   and for branches when the immediate sign bit is 1 (backward branch).\\n   On a predicted-taken instruction, redirect next_pc to pc+imm instead\\n   of pc+4. This means the sequential fall-through instruction is never\\n   fetched, so no flush is needed on a correct prediction.\\n3. In id_stage, pass predict_taken through the ID/EX register.\\n4. In ex_stage, change the redirect condition so it only fires on a\\n   mispredict: for branches when branch_taken != predict_taken, and for\\n   jumps when predict_taken == 0 (i.e. JALR, which is never predicted).\\n   Correctly predicted JALs and backward branches therefore flow through\\n   the pipeline with zero bubble penalty.\\n\\nThis is a much simpler and lower-risk version of the broken 32-entry\\ndynamic-PHT attempt: no stateful structures, no PHT update logic, and a\\ntiny combinational path (opcode compare → imm mux → adder) that reuses\\nthe existing pc+4 adder delay budget.\\n', 'expected_impact': {'fitness_delta_pct': 8, 'confidence': 'medium'}, 'changes': [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n'}]}\nid: len=21\nimplementation_notes: len=0\nipc_coremark: 2e-06\niterations: 10\nlut4: 10047\nmotivation: len=624\noutcome: len=10\nround_id: 2\nscribe_skipped: len=41\nse