 a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\\na single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\\nthe branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\\n', 'hypothesis': \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped BTB to the IF stage.\\n- Read: combinational, indexed by pc[6:2], outputs hit and target[31:0].\\n- Write: registered in EX when a conditional branch or JAL is resolved\\n  taken, storing pc[6:2] -> target.\\n- IF stage: next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target : btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4.\\n- Pipeline a predict_taken bit (= btb_hit) through IF/ID and ID/EX.\\n- EX stage: mispredict = (predict_taken != actual_taken). Redirect only on\\n  mispredict; correct BTB hits flow through with zero bubble. JALR is never\\n  predicted (target depends on rs1).\\nCoreMark's inner loops quickly warm the BTB, after which every loop-back\\nbranch costs zero bubbles instead of two. The BTB read path is shorter than\\nthe previous static predictor's imem_data->decode->adder path, so Fmax\\nimpact should be minimal.\\n\", 'expected_impact': {'fitness_delta_pct': 8, 'confidence': 'medium'}, 'changes': [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/btb.sv', 'description': 'New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en, update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.'}, {'file': 'rtl/core.sv', 'description': 'Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken through the pipeline bundles.'}]}\nid: len=21\nimplementation_notes: len=0\nipc_coremark: 2e-06\niterations: 10\nlut4: 10217\nmotivation: len=732\noutcome: len=10\nround_id: 3\nseeds: [146.07, 134.99, 141.58]\nslot: 2\ntimestamp: len=27\ntitle: len=72\nvs_baseline: 11.46\n","metadata":{"output":"---\ncategory: len=9\nchanges: [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv', 'description': 'Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.'}, {'file': 'rtl/branch_predictor.sv', 'description': 'New 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter PHT module with async read and synchronous update.'}, {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv', 'description': 'Add branch/JAL detection, imm_gen instance, target adder, and predictor integration to compute next_pc. Output predict_taken in IF/ID bundle.'}, {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv', 'description': 'Pass predict_taken from IF/ID into the ID/EX register.'}, {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'description': 'Change redirect logic to compare predicted vs actual outcome. Add predictor update output ports (update_en, update_pc, update_taken).'}, {'file': 'rtl/core.sv', 'description': 'Instantiate branch_predictor, wire update signals from EX stage to predictor, and pass predict_taken through the pipeline.'}]\ncosim_passed: False\nerror: len=4027\nexpected_impact: {'fitness_delta_pct': 10, 'confidence': 'medium'}\nformal_passed: False\nhypothesis: {'motivation': 'The baseline always fetches pc+4 and only redirects after a branch resolves in EX,\\ncosting a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch. CoreMark is loop-heavy; even a\\nsimple dynamic predictor eliminates most of these bubbles, directly improving IPC.\\nA 32-entry PHT adds only 64 flops and a small combinational read port, well within\\nthe ~400 LUT4 headroom on the Tang Nano 20K.\\n', 'hypothesis': 'Add a 32-entry 2-bit saturating counter 