{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778761622501,"sessionID":"ses_1d9986e98ffeo1wc7H48Yz9fNk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:25","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\ntitle: 64-entry tagged BTB inlined in IF with mispredict-only redirect\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Dynamic profiling shows CoreMark executes ~360k taken control-flow\n  instructions (branches + JAL + JALR) out of 2.9M total instructions.\n  The baseline always predicts not-taken, paying a 2-cycle bubble for\n  every one of them.  Eliminating these bubbles would cut ~718k cycles\n  from the 4.5M-cycle run, yielding a ~16% IPC improvement.\n\n  A prior 32-entry direct-mapped BTB attempt produced exactly zero\n  fitness delta with identical LUT/Fmax numbers, strongly suggesting the\n  BTB was synthesized away because the update path or the next-pc mux\n  was not wired correctly.  This hypothesis inlines the BTB directly\n  into if_stage.sv (no separate module to forget to instantiate), adds\n  a partial tag to avoid aliasing, and explicitly spells out the exact\n  next-pc expression and the pc+4 mispredict-recovery path so the\n  implementation agent cannot leave it as a no-op.\nhypothesis: |\n  Inline a 64-entry direct-mapped branch-target buffer into the IF stage.\n  Each entry stores a valid bit, a 24-bit tag (pc[31:8]), and a 32-bit\n  target.  The read is combinational: index = pc[7:2], hit = valid &&\n  (tag == pc[31:8]).  The write is synchronous and driven from the\n  EX/MEM register via top-level wiring in core.sv.\n\n  1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\n  2. In if_stage.sv, declare three parallel arrays btb_valid[0:63],\n     btb_tag[0:63][23:0], btb_target[0:63][31:0].  On reset clear all\n     valid bits.  Combinational read produces btb_hit and btb_target.\n     Override next_pc as:\n       next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target\n                          : (btb_hit ? btb_target : pc + 4);\n     Set out.predict_taken = btb_hit.\n     Add input ports btb_update_en, btb_update_pc[31:0],\n     btb_update_target[31:0] and register the write on the posedge.\n  3. In id_stage.sv, latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\n  4. In ex_stage.sv, replace the unconditional redirect with\n     mispredict-only redirect:\n       actual_taken = branch_taken || in.ctrl.is_jump;\n       redirect     = (actual_taken != in.predict_taken) && !misalign_fault;\n       redirect_target = (in.predict_taken && !actual_taken) ? (in.pc + 4)\n                         : in.ctrl.is_jump ? jump_target\n                         : branch_target;\n     This correctly recovers to pc+4 when a stale BTB entry predicted\n     taken but the branch is actually not taken.\n  5. In core.sv, compute the BTB update directly from the EX/MEM\n     register (no new ex_stage ports):\n       btb_update_en = ex_mem_w.valid && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_illegal &&\n                       ((ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_branch && ex_mem_w.branch_taken) ||\n                        (ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jump && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jalr));\n       btb_update_pc = ex_mem_w.pc;\n       btb_update_target = ex_mem_w.pc_next;\n     Wire these to the new if_stage ports.  The existing if_id_w struct\n     automatically carries predict_taken to the ID stage.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 10\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add logic predict_taken to if_id_t and id_ex_t structs.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Inline 64-entry BTB (btb_valid/tag/target arrays). Combinational\n      read indexed by pc[7:2]; synchronous update from new input ports.\n      Override next_pc = btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4. Drive\n      out.predict_taken = btb_hit. Clear valid bits on reset.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Change redirect to mispredict-only (XOR of predict_taken and\n      actual_taken). On a mispredict where predicted-taken but not-taken,\n      redirect_target must be pc+4. Keep misalign_fault suppression.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Derive BTB update enable/PC/target from ex_mem_w signals and wire\n      them to the new if_stage ports. No new ex_stage outputs needed.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778761622491,"end":1778761622500}},"id":"prt_e26741c1d001QGac06UT0VwK7O","sessionID":"ses_1d9986e98ffeo1wc7H48Yz9fNk","messageID":"msg_e2670e89c001k9CDyJzzBu6cFx"}}
