0: ##   0:00:38  Assert failed in rvfi_testbench: rvfi_insn_check.sv:198.6-198.31 (_witness_.check_flatten_checker_inst__assert_rvfi_insn_check_sv_198_153)\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:38  Writing trace to VCD file: engine_0/trace.vcd\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:38  Writing trace to Verilog testbench: engine_0/trace_tb.v\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:38  Writing trace to constraints file: engine_0/trace.smtc\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:38  Writing trace to Yosys witness file: engine_0/trace.yw\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:38  Status: failed\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=1)\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: FAIL\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:39 (39)\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:29 (29)\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned FAIL\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] summary: counterexample trace: insn_beq_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] summary:   failed assertion rvfi_testbench._witness_.check_flatten_checker_inst__assert_rvfi_insn_check_sv_198_153 at rvfi_insn_check.sv:198.6-198.31 step 20\\nSBY  7:46:06 [insn_beq_ch0] DONE (FAIL, rc=0)\\n\\nFull run log: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-003-r1s2/formal/last_run-43013.log\\nPer-check logs in: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-003-r1s2/formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench-43013/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r2s2\", \"title\": \"Static backward-taken predictor with early JAL resolution in IF\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\\nincurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately\\u2014eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline fetches sequentially and resolves all control flow in EX,\\nincurring a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and unconditional jump.\\nCoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward conditional branches (loop edges)\\ndominate the dynamic branch count. A purely static predictor that predicts\\nJAL as always-taken and backward branches as taken requires no stateful\\ntable, no PHT updates, and minimal combinational logic in the IF stage.\\nBecause the prediction is computed from the instruction already on the\\nimem_data bus, the target can be fetched immediately\\u2014eliminating the\\nredirect bubble entirely for correct predictions.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add combinational branch/jump prediction to the IF stage and suppress\\nEX-stage redirects when the prediction is correct.\\n\\n1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\\n2. In if_stage, instantiate a small imm_gen (or inline equivalent) to\\n   extract the B/J immediate from imem_data. Detect opcode 1100011\\n   (BRANCH) and 1101111 (JAL). Predict taken for JAL unconditionally,\\n   and for branches when the immediate sign bit is 1 (backward branch).\\n   On a predicted-taken instruction, redirect next_pc to pc+imm instead\\n   of pc+4. This means the sequential fall-through instruction is never\\n   fetched, so no flush is needed on a correct prediction.\\n3. In id_stage, pass predict_taken through the ID/EX register.\\n4. In ex_stage, change the redirect condition so it only fires on a\\n   mispredict: for branches when branch_taken != predict_taken, and for\\n   jumps when predict_taken == 0 (i.e. JALR, which is never predicted).\\n   Correctly predicted JALs and backward branches therefore flow through\\n   the pipeline with zero bubble penalty.\\n\\nThis is a much simpler and lower-risk version of the broken 32-entry\\ndynamic-PHT attempt: no stateful structures, no PHT update logic, and a\\ntiny combinational path (opcode compare \\u2192 imm mux \\u2192 adder) that reuses\\nthe existing pc+4 adder delay budget.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add imm_gen instance (or inline immediate extraction) for B/J types. Detect BRANCH and JAL opcodes. Compute target = pc + imm. Drive next_pc to target when predicted taken, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken for valid predicted-taken instructions.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional redirect on taken branches/jumps with mispredict-only redirect: redirect when a branch outcome differs from predict_taken, or when a jump was not predicted taken (JALR). Keep misalign_fault suppression unchanged.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 203.63, \"delta_pct\": -35.4, \"vs_baseline\": -28.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 86.74, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10047, \"ff\": 1868, \"seeds\": [86.74, 87.03, 82.66], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:19:46.077886Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 2, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"32-entry direct-mapped BTB in IF stage to eliminate taken-branch bubbles\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches sequentially, paying a 2-cycle bubble for every\\ntaken branch and JAL. A prior static predictor that computed branch targets\\ncombinationally in IF from imem_data (decode -> imm_gen -> adder) slashed\\nFmax by ~40% because that path starts from the off-chip/BRAM instruction\\nword. A Branch Target Buffer (BTB) avoids that path entirely: it is indexed\\ndirectly by the PC register output, so the predicted next PC is just a small\\ndistributed-RAM read with no instruction decode or adder in the critical\\npath. On the Tang Nano 20K a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\\na single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\\nthe branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The baseline always fetches sequentially, paying a 2-cycle bubble for every\\ntaken branch and JAL. A prior static predictor that computed branch targets\\ncombinationally in IF from imem_data (decode -> imm_gen -> adder) slashed\\nFmax by ~40% because that path starts from the off-chip/BRAM instruction\\nword. A Branch Target Buffer (BTB) avoids that path entirely: it is indexed\\ndirectly by the PC register output, so the predicted next PC is just a small\\ndistributed-RAM read with no instruction decode or adder in the critical\\npath. On the Tang Nano 20K a 32-entry BTB costs only ~35 LUTs and reads in\\na single LUT delay, making it a much safer timing bet while still removing\\nthe branch bubble for loop-back edges once they warm up.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped BTB to the IF stage.\\n- Read: combinational, indexed by pc[6:2], outputs hit and target[31:0].\\n- Write: registered in EX when a conditional branch or JAL is resolved\\n  taken, storing pc[6:2] -> target.\\n- IF stage: next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target : btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4.\\n- Pipeline a predict_taken bit (= btb_hit) through IF/ID and ID/EX.\\n- EX stage: mispredict = (predict_taken != actual_taken). Redirect only on\\n  mispredict; correct BTB hits flow through with zero bubble. JALR is never\\n  predicted (target depends on rs1).\\nCoreMark's inner loops quickly warm the BTB, after which every loop-back\\nbranch costs zero bubbles instead of two. The BTB read path is shorter than\\nthe previous static predictor's imem_data->decode->adder path, so Fmax\\nimpact should be minimal.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/btb.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en, update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken through the pipeline bundles.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predict_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/btb.sv\", \"description\": \"New 32-entry direct-mapped branch target buffer. Combinational read indexed by pc[6:2]; registered write on taken branch/jump resolution from EX. Each entry holds a valid bit and a 30-bit word-aligned target.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Query the BTB with the current PC. Drive next_pc to btb_target on a hit, otherwise pc+4. Set out.predict_taken when the BTB hits.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compare predicted vs actual branch/jump outcome and assert redirect only on mispredict. Drive BTB update signals (update_en, update_pc, update_target) for taken branches and JAL.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate the BTB module, wire its read ports to the IF stage, and wire its update ports from the EX stage. Pass predict_taken through the pipeline bundles.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 315.22, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 11.46, \"fmax_mhz\": 141.58, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10217, \"ff\": 1864, \"seeds\": [146.07, 134.99, 141.58], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T11:48:15.113672Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\", \"title\": \"64-entry tagged BTB inlined in IF with mispredict-only redirect\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"Dynamic profiling shows CoreMark executes ~360k taken control-flow\\ninstructions (branches + JAL + JALR) out of 2.9M total instructions.\\nThe baseline always predicts not-taken, paying a 2-cycle bubble for\\nevery one of them.  Eliminating these bubbles would cut ~718k cycles\\nfrom the 4.5M-cycle run, yielding a ~16% IPC improvement.\\n\\nA prior 32-entry direct-mapped BTB attempt produced exactly zero\\nfitness delta with identical LUT/Fmax numbers, strongly suggesting the\\nBTB was synthesized away because the update path or the next-pc mux\\nwas not wired correctly.  This hypothesis inlines the BTB directly\\ninto if_stage.sv (no separate module to forget to instantiate), adds\\na partial tag to avoid aliasing, and explicitly spells out the exact\\nnext-pc expression and the pc+4 mispredict-recovery path so the\\nimplementation agent cannot leave it as a no-op.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Dynamic profiling shows CoreMark executes ~360k taken control-flow\\ninstructions (branches + JAL + JALR) out of 2.9M total instructions.\\nThe baseline always predicts not-taken, paying a 2-cycle bubble for\\nevery one of them.  Eliminating these bubbles would cut ~718k cycles\\nfrom the 4.5M-cycle run, yielding a ~16% IPC improvement.\\n\\nA prior 32-entry direct-mapped BTB attempt produced exactly zero\\nfitness delta with identical LUT/Fmax numbers, strongly suggesting the\\nBTB was synthesized away because the update path or the next-pc mux\\nwas not wired correctly.  This hypothesis inlines the BTB directly\\ninto if_stage.sv (no separate module to forget to instantiate), adds\\na partial tag to avoid aliasing, and explicitly spells out the exact\\nnext-pc expression and the pc+4 mispredict-recovery path so the\\nimplementation agent cannot leave it as a no-op.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Inline a 64-entry direct-mapped branch-target buffer into the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a valid bit, a 24-bit tag (pc[31:8]), and a 32-bit\\ntarget.  The read is combinational: index = pc[7:2], hit = valid &&\\n(tag == pc[31:8]).  The write is synchronous and driven from the\\nEX/MEM register via top-level wiring in core.sv.\\n\\n1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single predict_taken bit.\\n2. In if_stage.sv, declare three parallel arrays btb_valid[0:63],\\n   btb_tag[0:63][23:0], btb_target[0:63][31:0].  On reset clear all\\n   valid bits.  Combinational read produces btb_hit and btb_target.\\n   Override next_pc as:\\n     next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target\\n                        : (btb_hit ? btb_target : pc + 4);\\n   Set out.predict_taken = btb_hit.\\n   Add input ports btb_update_en, btb_update_pc[31:0],\\n   btb_update_target[31:0] and register the write on the posedge.\\n3. In id_stage.sv, latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\\n4. In ex_stage.sv, replace the unconditional redirect with\\n   mispredict-only redirect:\\n     actual_taken = branch_taken || in.ctrl.is_jump;\\n     redirect     = (actual_taken != in.predict_taken) && !misalign_fault;\\n     redirect_target = (in.predict_taken && !actual_taken) ? (in.pc + 4)\\n                       : in.ctrl.is_jump ? jump_target\\n                       : branch_target;\\n   This correctly recovers to pc+4 when a stale BTB entry predicted\\n   taken but the branch is actually not taken.\\n5. In core.sv, compute the BTB update directly from the EX/MEM\\n   register (no new ex_stage ports):\\n     btb_update_en = ex_mem_w.valid && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_illegal &&\\n                     ((ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_branch && ex_mem_w.branch_taken) ||\\n                      (ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jump && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jalr));\\n     btb_update_pc = ex_mem_w.pc;\\n     btb_update_target = ex_mem_w.pc_next;\\n   Wire these to the new if_stage ports.  The existing if_id_w struct\\n   automatically carries predict_taken to the ID stage.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic predict_taken to if_id_t and id_ex_t structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Inline 64-entry BTB (btb_valid/tag/target arrays). Combinational\\nread indexed by pc[7:2]; synchronous update from new input ports.\\nOverride next_pc = btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4. Drive\\nout.predict_taken = btb_hit. Clear valid bits on reset.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Change redirect to mispredict-only (XOR of predict_taken and\\nactual_taken). On a mispredict where predicted-taken but not-taken,\\nredirect_target must be pc+4. Keep misalign_fault suppression.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Derive BTB update enable/PC/target from ex_mem_w signals and wire\\nthem to the new if_stage ports. No new ex_stage outputs needed.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add logic predict_taken to if_id_t and id_ex_t structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Inline 64-entry BTB (btb_valid/tag/target arrays). Combinational\\nread indexed by pc[7:2]; synchronous update from new input ports.\\nOverride next_pc = btb_hit ? btb_target : pc+4. Drive\\nout.predict_taken = btb_hit. Clear valid bits on reset.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Change redirect to mispredict-only (XOR of predict_taken and\\nactual_taken). On a mispredict where predicted-taken but not-taken,\\nredirect_target must be pc+4. Keep misalign_fault suppression.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Derive BTB update enable/PC/target from ex_mem_w signals and wire\\nthem to the new if_stage ports. No new ex_stage outputs needed.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"formal_failed: pc_fwd_ch0\\n: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 10:12:18 [insn_bge_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:14:27 (867)\\nSBY 10:12:18 [insn_bge_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:14:07 (847)\\nSBY 10:12:18 [insn_bge_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 10:12:18 [insn_bge_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 10:12:18 [insn_bge_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:14:36  Status: passed\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:14:37 (877)\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:14:18 (858)\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY 10:12:29 [insn_bltu_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\n\\nFormal: 52 passed, 1 failed\\nFailed: pc_fwd_ch0\\n\\n--- pc_fwd_ch0/logfile.txt (last 30 lines) ---\\nSBY  9:57:49 [pc_fwd_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 8..\\nSBY  9:57