{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778765086196,"sessionID":"ses_1d95e7ea7ffeCzJ7R13c6WKCnU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r5s2\ntitle: 16-entry inlined BTB with explicit RVFI-safe mispredict-only redirect\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline pays a 2-cycle bubble for every taken branch and JAL because\n  it always fetches PC+4 and redirects only after EX resolution. Prior\n  attempts to add a BTB either produced zero fitness delta (identical LUT/FF\n  counts prove the structure was synthesized away because the update path was\n  disconnected) or broke rvfi_pc_fwd (the implementation agent altered\n  EX/MEM.pc_next to depend on redirect, so a correct prediction reported\n  PC+4 instead of the actual target). A very small, explicitly inlined BTB\n  avoids module-instantiation mistakes, and spelling out the exact combinational\n  changes in ex_stage.sv with a bold “do not touch pc_next” rule should finally\n  let the predictor actually fire without corrupting the architectural trace.\n  CoreMark is loop-heavy; even a 16-entry table should capture the handful of\n  hot backward edges and JAL targets that dominate dynamic control flow.\nhypothesis: |\n  Inline a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB directly inside if_stage.sv (no separate\n  module to forget to instantiate). Use EX/MEM register signals for update in\n  core.sv so no new ex_stage outputs are needed. Only two combinational lines\n  in ex_stage.sv change—redirect and redirect_target—while the EX/MEM register\n  pc_next assignment is left verbatim so RVFI pc_wdata stays architecturally\n  correct.\n\n  1. Extend if_id_t and id_ex_t with a single logic predict_taken bit.\n  2. In if_stage.sv, declare three parallel arrays:\n       btb_valid [0:15]\n       btb_tag   [0:15][25:0]   // pc[31:6]\n       btb_target[0:15][31:0]\n     On reset clear all valid bits. Combinational read:\n       btb_hit   = btb_valid[pc[5:2]] && (btb_tag[pc[5:2]] == pc[31:6]);\n       btb_target_out = btb_target[pc[5:2]];\n     PC selection:\n       next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target\n                        : (btb_hit ? btb_target_out : pc + 32'd4);\n     IF/ID output:\n       out.predict_taken = btb_hit && !(flush || redirect);\n     Add three new input ports to if_stage:\n       btb_update_en, btb_update_pc[31:0], btb_update_target[31:0]\n     Register the write on the posedge clock when btb_update_en is asserted:\n       btb_valid[btb_update_pc[5:2]]   <= 1'b1;\n       btb_tag  [btb_update_pc[5:2]]   <= btb_update_pc[31:6];\n       btb_target[btb_update_pc[5:2]]  <= btb_update_target;\n  3. In id_stage.sv, latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\n  4. In ex_stage.sv make ONLY the following combinational changes and\n     DO NOT modify the always_ff block that writes reg_q.pc_next:\n       // Redirect only when prediction ≠ actual outcome.\n       assign redirect = ((branch_taken != in.predict_taken) ||\n                          (in.ctrl.is_jump && !in.predict_taken))\n                         && !misalign_fault;\n       // Recovery target: if we predicted taken but the branch is not taken,\n       // go to the fall-through PC+4; otherwise use the normal jump/branch\n       // target.\n       assign redirect_target =\n         (in.predict_taken && !branch_taken && !in.ctrl.is_jump)\n           ? (in.pc + 32'd4)\n           : (in.ctrl.is_jump ? jump_target : branch_target);\n     // CRITICAL: reg_q.pc_next must keep the baseline expression that uses\n     // actual branch_taken / is_jump / jump_target, independent of predict_taken\n     // or redirect. This preserves rvfi_pc_fwd correctness.\n  5. In core.sv derive BTB update straight from the EX/MEM register:\n       logic btb_update_en;\n       logic [31:0] btb_update_pc;\n       logic [31:0] btb_update_target;\n       assign btb_update_en = ex_mem_w.valid && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_illegal &&\n         ((ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_branch && ex_mem_w.branch_taken) ||\n          (ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jump && !ex_mem_w.ctrl.is_jalr));\n       assign btb_update_pc     = ex_mem_w.pc;\n       assign btb_update_target = ex_mem_w.pc_next;\n     Wire these to the new if_stage ports and pass predict_taken through the\n     existing if_id_w / id_ex_w pipeline bundles.\n\n  Because the BTB is indexed by the PC register output, the read path is a\n  tiny distributed-RAM lookup with no instruction-decode or adder on the\n  critical imem_data path. The 16-entry size keeps LUT/FF cost low so Fmax\n  impact should be negligible; meanwhile every correctly predicted taken branch\n  or JAL removes two full bubble cycles.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add logic predict_taken to if_id_t and id_ex_t structs.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Inline 16-entry BTB arrays (valid, tag, target). Combinational read\n      indexed by pc[5:2]; synchronous update via new input ports.\n      Override next_pc with btb_target on hit, otherwise pc+4.\n      Drive out.predict_taken = btb_hit when not flushing.\n      Clear valid bits on reset.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: Latch in.predict_taken into the ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Make ONLY two combinational assign changes: redirect becomes\n      mispredict-only (XOR of predict_taken and actual outcome), and\n      redirect_target selects pc+4 for a predicted-taken / not-taken\n      mispredict. DO NOT touch the always_ff block that writes reg_q.pc_next;\n      it must remain based on actual branch_taken / is_jump / jump_target.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Derive btb_update_en, btb_update_pc, and btb_update_target from the\n      ex_mem_w register fields and wire them to the new if_stage ports.\n      Pass predict_taken through the existing pipeline bundles.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r5s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778765086190,"end":1778765086196}},"id":"prt_e26a89680001DBa6TTIVat2Nng","sessionID":"ses_1d95e7ea7ffeCzJ7R13c6WKCnU","messageID":"msg_e26a7d52a001Twu5cu1zeFY2uN"}}
