{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778766823836,"sessionID":"ses_1d93f66fcffeU3HoPsmzI5WHOS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r6s2\ntitle: Static BTFN predictor in IF with mispredict-only redirect in EX\n\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline always predicts not-taken, paying a 2-cycle flush penalty on every\n  taken branch and every JAL. CoreMark is loop-heavy and makes frequent function\n  calls, so backward branches and JALs are a large fraction of dynamic control-flow.\n  A stateless Backward-Taken / Forward-Not-taken (BTFN) predictor costs almost no\n  state, adds only a small amount of combinational logic in the IF stage, and can\n  eliminate the flush penalty on loop back-edges and unconditional jumps.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a BTFN predictor to the IF stage:\n    - JAL is always predicted taken (target = PC + JAL imm, known in IF).\n    - Conditional branches are predicted taken only when their immediate is negative\n      (backward branch), otherwise not-taken.\n    - JALR is not predicted (falls through) because the target depends on a register\n      value not visible in IF.\n    - The predicted target is validated in the same cycle it is produced; if the\n      computed target is misaligned ([1:0] != 0) the prediction is suppressed and\n      IF falls back to PC+4, matching the trap-and-fallthrough semantics.\n\n  Change the EX-stage redirect semantics from \"taken branch/jump\" to \"mispredict\":\n    - EX always computes the architecturally correct next-PC (pc_next / pc_wdata)\n      from the actual branch/jump resolution, independent of prediction.\n    - redirect is asserted only when the actual outcome differs from the BTFN\n      prediction (JALR always mispredicts, backward branches mispredict when not\n      taken, forward branches mispredict when taken).\n    - redirect_target is driven from the actual resolved target, not the prediction.\n    - This preserves RVFI correctness because pc_wdata never depends on the\n      predictor state.\n\n  With this change, correctly predicted JALs and loop-back branches cost 0 flush\n  cycles instead of 2, directly improving CoreMark IPC.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 7\n  confidence: medium\n\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Insert BTFN prediction combinational logic before the PC register.\n      Compute JAL target and BRANCH target from the raw fetched instruction.\n      Drive next_pc from the predicted target for JAL and backward branches,\n      unless the target is misaligned. Pass no extra state through the pipeline\n      bundle; EX recomputes the prediction locally.\n\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Replace redirect = (branch_taken || is_jump) with mispredict detection:\n      JAL is never a mispredict, JALR is always a mispredict, conditional\n      branches mispredict when branch_taken != imm[31]. Drive redirect_target\n      and pc_next from the actual resolved target (same as architectural next-PC).\n      Ensure misalign_fault still suppresses redirect and forces pc_next = PC+4.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778766823820,"end":1778766823834}},"id":"prt_e26c39a60001IOKBVPNw7J7cAk","sessionID":"ses_1d93f66fcffeU3HoPsmzI5WHOS","messageID":"msg_e26c0993d00161Z95JRVMXszcT"}}
