{"type":"text","timestamp":1778766844224,"sessionID":"ses_1d93f66fcffeU3HoPsmzI5WHOS","part":{"id":"prt_e26c3ef710017LyEACj2vG6WEE","messageID":"msg_e26c3d117001tdrivYJRYyhrwJ","sessionID":"ses_1d93f66fcffeU3HoPsmzI5WHOS","type":"text","text":"Done. The hypothesis has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** predictor\n- **Approach:** Add a stateless BTFN (Backward-Taken / Forward-Not-taken) predictor in IF that predicts JAL always-taken and backward branches taken. EX stage is changed to assert `redirect` only on mispredict, while always reporting the true architectural `pc_wdata` for RVFI safety.\n- **Why it should help:** CoreMark is loop-heavy; eliminating the 2-cycle flush penalty on loop back-edges and function calls should raise IPC with minimal Fmax risk (no extra state tables, just lightweight immediate extraction and adders in IF).\n- **Expected impact:** +7% fitness, medium confidence.","time":{"start":1778766835569,"end":1778766844221}}}
