{"type":"text","timestamp":1778769928364,"sessionID":"ses_1d9115ac5ffeknEhJisfIiSeQ3","part":{"id":"prt_e26f2f5a400146PDwDBVMQzKdV","messageID":"msg_e26f2d4c5002vIT5KqKjKiXHjk","sessionID":"ses_1d9115ac5ffeknEhJisfIiSeQ3","type":"text","text":"I've written the hypothesis YAML for **hyp-20260514-003-r7s2** to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the proposal:**\n\n- **Concept:** Add an 8-entry direct-mapped BTB inline in `if_stage.sv`, indexed by `pc[4:2]` (same indexing as the existing I-cache). It stores targets for taken branches and JALs.\n- **Why this should work:** Prior static predictors that computed targets from `imem_data` killed Fmax by ~40%. A PC-indexed BTB avoids that critical path entirely. Prior BTB attempts failed due to redirect/RVFI bugs, not the concept.\n- **Key safeguards against known failures:**\n  1. `next_pc` in IF **preserves** the existing `redirect` path; prediction is an overlay, not a replacement. This avoids the `pc_fwd` trap from r6s2.\n  2. EX-stage `pc_next` is kept **exactly as baseline**, computed from actual branch/jump resolution. Only the `redirect` signal changes to mispredict-only. This avoids the `rvfi_pc_fwd` trap from r4s2/r5s2.\n  3. Branch and jump mispredict checks are **separate**, so JAL (always taken) is never compared against `branch_taken`. This avoids the false-mispredict trap from r5s2.\n- **Expected impact:** ~10% fitness improvement (medium confidence), driven by eliminating 2-cycle bubbles for loop-back branches and JAL targets once they warm up in the BTB.","time":{"start":1778769917348,"end":1778769928362}}}
